<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>DCCA: Office of Minority Business Development -- Black-owned Business Facts</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000080" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#8080C0" ALINK="#8080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/logosm.jpg" alt="DCCA Logo" width=165 height=82 align=left>
<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4><p>
<h3>
Department of Commerce & Community Affairs<p>
</h3>
<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4><p>
<FONT SIZE=+3>Office of Minority Business Development</FONT>
<BR CLEAR=RIGHT>
<HR>

<h3 align=center>
Fact Sheet<br>
Black-Owned Business in Illinois
</h3>

Based upon a U.S. Bureau of the Census report, black-owned businesses in Illinois have increased from 19,011 in 1987 to 28,433 in 1992 for a gain of 49.6 percent. Sales also rose from $1.1 billion to $1.8 billion, rising 61.2 percent during the period.<p>

According to the report, Black-Owned businesses numbered 26,644 in the Chicago metropolitan area during 1992, compared to 15,374 in 1987. This spectacular growth ranked the Chicago metropolitan area fourth in the country next to New York, Washington, D.C. and Los Angeles. The report also indicates that Illinois' largest county, Cook, placed second nationally among the 10 largest counties with 21,937 black-owned firms.<p>
 
The largest category of Black-Owned industries in Illinois during 1992 were: services with 14,638 firms or 51.5 percent followed by retail sales with 4,209 companies and 14.8 percent. Substantial gains were also reported in the transportation and construction industries.<p>

<h3 align=center>BLACK-OWNED BUSINESS GROWTH IN ILLINOIS</h3>
<center><pre>
<strong>                            1987                               1992
                  Number     Receipts                 Number      Receipts</strong><p>
Illinois             19,011     $1.1 billion             28,433     $1.8 billion
Chicago metro area   15,374     $908.5 million           24,644     $1.6 billion
Cook County          15,011     $871.5 million           21,937     $1.4 billion
Chicago               11,156     $670.4 million           15,328     $1.1 billion 
</pre>

<em>Source: U.S. Bureau of the Census - 1992 Economic Census, Survey of Minority-Owned Business Enterprises.</em><p></center>
 
Office of Minority Business Development<br>
Illinois Department of Commerce and Community Affairs<br>
James R. Thompson Center<br>
100 West Randolph Street, Suite 3-400 <br>
Chicago, Illinois 60610<br>
312/814-3540 or 814-2331; Fax: 312/814-5247<br>
World Wide Web: <a href="http://www.ilcommerce.com">http://www.ilcommerce.com</a><p>

Developed through a partnership between the U.S. Small Business Administration and the Illinois Department of Commerce and Community Affairs under cooperative agreement # SB-2M-00097-13<p>

