<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>DCCA: Energy Programs</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000080" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#8080C0" ALINK="#8080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/logosm.jpg" alt="DCCA Logo" width=165 height=82 align=left>
<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4><p>
<h3>
Department of Commerce & Community Affairs<p>
</h3>
<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4><p>
<font size=+3>Programs and Services</font>
<br clear=right>
<hr>

<CENTER><H2>Energy Programs</H2></CENTER>
<HR>

<H3><a href="../enr/ethanol.htm"> Ethanol Demonstration Program</a></H3>
<DL><DD>
     DCCA manages numerous ethanol demonstration projects to foster the
     usage of ethanol, thus encouraging the relationship between industrial
     manufacturing and rural development.  In addition, DCCA supports the
     research and development of new technologies to reduce the cost of
     producing ethanol.<P>

     For information call 217/785-3969.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>Affordable Housing</H3>
<DL><DD>
     DCCA provides grants and technical assistance to developers upgrading
     or building new housing units to ensure that the dwellings incorporate
     the latest in energy conservation techniques, thus lowering energy
     usage and costs for low-and moderate-income Illinoisans.<P>

     For information call 217/785-2373.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3><a href="../enr/enwise.htm"> "EnergyWise Homes of Illinois"</a></H3>
<DL><DD>
     Promotes a home energy ratings system to help builders and homeowners
     understand the overall energy costs associated with a home and help
     them make informed choices about energy products when building or
     remodeling homes.<P>

     For information call 217/785-2007.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>Energy Performance Contracting</H3>
<DL><DD>
     DCCA staffers provide counseling to help arrange innovative financing
     for energy improvement projects.  Under the arrangements, savings
     generated by the project are guaranteed to amortize the project over
     the life of the agreement, which is usually 10 years.<P>

     For information call 217/785-3996.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>Energy Efficiency in State Buildings Program</H3>
<DL><DD>
     Operators of state buildings are provided energy engineering
     assistance and ongoing energy efficiency training.<P>

     For information call 217/785-2765.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>Institutional Conservation Program</H3>
<DL><DD>
     Matching grants are provided to schools and hospitals to help reduce
     energy consumption.  Technical Assistance Grants help institutions
     hire architects or engineers to complete detailed energy studies.
     Energy Conservation Measures grants provide funds for the actual
     retrofits.<P>

     For information call 217/785-3983.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>Telecommuting Program</H3>
<DL><DD>
     DCCA works with industries, businesses and not-for-profit
     organizations to promote telecommuting as an innovative transportation
     alternative.<P>

     For information call 312/814-3485.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>Energy Emergency Preparedness</H3>
<DL><DD>
     DCCA provides direct energy emergency preparedness support to the
     Illinois Emergency Management Agency (IEMA) during emergency and
     disaster situations.<P>

     For information call 312/814-3485.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3><a href="../../menus/ileed.htm"> Illinois Energy Education Development (ILEED)</a></H3>
<DL><DD>
     ILEED is an effective energy and environmental education program for
     children in grades K through 12.<P>

     For information call 217/785-3411.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3><a href="../enr/intern.htm"> High School Internships</a></H3>
<DL><DD>
     DCCA sponsors internships for high school students who work as paid
     professionals with energy and environmental organizations in their
     communities.<P>

     For information call 217/785-3411.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>Energy NET</H3>
<DL><DD>
     DCCA provides hands-on, in-depth energy management training to student
     and teacher representatives from Illinois high schools, utilizing
     interactive computer technologies.<P>

     For information call 217/785-3411.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>Partners in Environmental Education Program</H3>
<DL><DD>
     DCCA and The Illinois Chamber work together to encourage businesses
     and  schools to partner to promote environmental education.<P>

     For information call 217/785-3412.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <A HREF="http://www.ilcommerce.com">DCCA Home Page</A> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/programs.htm">Programs & Services</A> |</STRONG>
</BODY>
</HTML>
