<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>DCCA: Message from Governor Jim Edgar</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000080" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">


<img src="/dcca/graph/logosm.jpg" alt="DCCA Logo" width=165 height=82 align=left>
<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4><p>
<h3>
Department of Commerce & Community Affairs<p>
</h3>
<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4><p>
<font size=+3>Message from Governor Jim Edgar</font>
<br clear=right>
<hr>
<p>

<img src="graph/govedgar.gif" alt="Gov. Edgar Picture" width=113 height=156 hspace=20 vspace=20 align=left>
<h4>
Illinois is at the center of a Midwest economic renaissance spurred by many factors, including a state government that has been friendlier to business than any in 20 years.  The Illinois Department of Commerce and Community Affairs (DCCA) is leading the charge, helping companies find locations for their next expansion or location, unraveling red tape, training our productive workers, fostering the growth of small businesses, promoting environmentally-sound practices and helping improve quality of life through partnerships with local government to address infrastructure and human service needs.<p>

Over the past year, DCCA has received record numbers of inquiries from companies interested in expanding or locating in Illinois.  From ALCOA to Zenith, businesses are choosing Illinois for their major projects.  In fact, Industry Week magazine readers ranked Illinois first in the Midwest as the preferred destination for industry relocation. <p>

DCCA's web site is designed to provide you with a comprehensive look at the agency's many programs and services to promote economic development.  I invite you to investigate.  You can also access the <a href="http://www.state.il.us">State of Illinois home page</a> for more information about our great state.<p>
</h4>

<hr>
<STRONG>| <a href="home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> |</STRONG>
</BODY>

</HTML>

