</h4>

This show will highlight only U.S. made products and services. United States companies active in the following industry sectors will be highlighted:  hi-tech sectors, computer equipment and software, medical equipment and supplies, telecommunications, aviation and space technology, laser technology, and security equipment.  Visitors will be drawn from the entire European Community as well as parts of Central and Eastern Europe.<p>

<strong>Contact:</strong> Charles Reed, 312/814-2091; TDD: 800/419-0667<p>

<hr>
<h4>
AUTOCHINA*<br>
June 1997<br>
Shanghai, China<p>
</h4>

Auto China'97 will be the 13th annual International Trade Show held in China since its inception in 1985.  Auto China is the largest exhibition of auto parts, accessories, and related manufacturing technology held in China.  With the tremendous growth of infrastructure development in the Asian Pacific countries, transportation technologies, equipment and parts are in tremendous demand.  This exhibition offers Illinois firms the opportunity to meet decision-makers in what is forecasted to be the 3rd largest automotive market in the world by 2010.<p>

<strong>Contact:</strong> Thomas W. Hagle, 312/814-4959; TDD: 800/419-0667<p>   

<strong>*</strong> MDCP Grant Program<p>

<hr>
<h4>"Crossing International Borders Conference"</h4>

Exporters and companies interested in exploring the global marketplace can get valuable tips to help them achieve success at this year's "Crossing International Borders" Conference, to be held at the Chicago Hilton and Towers on May 16.  The conference is co-sponsored by DCCA's International Business Division and Arthur Andersen.  Registration is $95 per person through May 9 or $125 per person following that date.  For conference information or registration, contact Mary Anne Brown-Rogerio at DCCA at 312/814-2325 (TDD: 312/419-0667).<p>


