<HEAD><TITLE>DCCA: Regulatory Flexibility</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000080" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#8080C0" ALINK="#8080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/logosm.jpg" alt="DCCA Logo" width=165 height=82 align=left>
<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4><p>
<h3>
Department of Commerce & Community Affairs<p>
</h3>
<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4><p>
<FONT SIZE=+3>Regulatory Flexibility</FONT>
<BR CLEAR=RIGHT>
<HR>

<h4>
Conducts impact analyses of proposed rules and regulations affecting the small business community and recommends ways of "tiering" or elminating rules deemed overly burdensome for small businesses. A Regulatory Flexibility Oversight Group, with representatives from major business and trade associations and the U.S. Small Business Administration, assists in conducting the analyses and facilitating awareness of business issues. As an advocate for small businesses, DCCA also monitors General Assembly activity for legislation introduced affecting these businesses.<p>

For more information, call 217/785-8021, or <a href="mailto:linda.brand@accessil.com">write us</a>.<p>
</h4>
<hr>
<h3>
<img src="../graph/button1.gif" width=27 height=34 align=middle> <a href="rfprop.htm">Proposed Regulations</a><p>
