<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop Business Information Center</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/dcca/graph/fs/firststopback.gif" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000000" VLINK="#0000A0" ALINK="#0000A0">

<table width=600>
<tr>
<td colspan=1 valign=top>


<table width=125 >
<td valign=top align=left>
<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fsdcca.gif"><p>
</td>
</table>


<td colspan=1 align=left>
<table width=475 >

<td valign=top><h3>
<center>
<h3>Illinois Department of Commerce & Community Affairs</h3>
<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/Fslogo2.GIF" alt="First Stop Logo" width=251 height=120>
<br clear=all>
<IMG SRC="/dcca/graph/fs/fsbar.gif">
</center>
<br clear=all>
<p>
<h4>

<h3><em>It's quick. It's simple. And it's free.</em><p></h3>
<h4>
Now, Illinois has a single, statewide resource to help individuals and businesses obtain comprehensive regulatory and permit information and referral assistance. By making it easy for businesses to get the information they need, First Stop enhances the economic climate in Illinois and helps companies stay competitive.<p>
</h4>

<h3><em>How can First Stop help your business?</em><p></h3>
<h4>
<em>For start-up businesses:</em> First Stop offers a detailed handbook, "Starting a Business in Illinois," that includes a feasibility checklist and business plan outline, as well as general business regulations and issues facing new business ventures. The handbook will be mailed free of charge upon request. Also, an abbreviated start-up guide is immediately available by fax.<p>

<em>For existing businesses:</em> First Stop identifies applicable regulations and services. First Stop's database inventories business licenses, certificates and registrations required by the State of Illinois.<p>

<em>For all businesses:</em> First Stop offers a directory of business requirements and assistance programs which identifies more than 500 requirements and assistance programs from more than 40 state agencies and constitutional offices. First Stop links your company to state services and assistance programs, from financing to free consulting, and provides information on how to apply for these programs.<p>
</h4>

<h3><em>Getting information from First Stop couldn't be easier.</em><p></h3>
<h4>
<em>Phone:</em> 800/252-2923 (statewide, toll-free) to be connected with a knowledgeable business specialist who can answer your questions and provide additional information by fax or U.S. mail.<p>

<em>Local access:</em> For online access and helpful advice from small business experts, visit your local Small Business Development Center (SBDC). SBDCs provide technical and management assistance to Illinois business owners through one-on-one counseling and group training sessions. Call First Stop for locations.<p>
<hr>
</h4>

<h3><center>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm"> DCCA Home</a> | <a href="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm"> First Stop</a> | </center></h3>
</TD>




</table>

</TABLE>

</BODY>
</HTML>
