<HEAD><TITLE>DCCA: Proposed Rules - December 6, 1996</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000080" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#8080C0" ALINK="#8080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/logosm.jpg" alt="DCCA Logo" width=165 height=82 align=left>
<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4><p>
<h3>
Department of Commerce & Community Affairs<p>
</h3>
<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4><p>
<font size=+3>Proposed Rules</font>
<hr>

<CENTER>
The proposed rules marked with an * are of particular interest to small
business and the department specifically requests comments on those issues.
Comments on any rule are encouraged.<P>
</CENTER>
<HR>
<h3 align=center>
Illinois Register<BR>
December 6, 1996
</h3>
<hr>

<h4>DEPARTMENT OF CHILDREN AND FAMILY SERVICES</h4>

<strong><em>Purchase of Service</em></strong> - Requires background checks on persons who provide day care services which are funded by the department. (New)<p>

<hr>
<h4>POLLUTION CONTROL BOARD *</h4>

<strong><em>Tiered Approach to Corrective Action Objectives</em></strong> - Establishes procedures for developing corrective action objectives for soil and groundwater at remediation sites, based on risks to human health and the environment.  Three levels of analysis.   (New)  (PA 89-431) (R 97-12)<p>

<hr>
<h4>DEPARTMENT OF REVENUE</h4>

<strong><em>Property Tax Code</em></strong> - Provides guidance to county clerks in notifying the department of the results on referenda regarding the applicability of  Property Tax Extension Limitation Law.  (New)  (Emergency)  (PA 89-510)<p>


