<HEAD><TITLE>DCCA: Proposed Rules - November 22, 1996</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000080" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#8080C0" ALINK="#8080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/logosm.jpg" alt="DCCA Logo" width=165 height=82 align=left>
<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4><p>
<h3>
Department of Commerce & Community Affairs<p>
</h3>
<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4><p>
<font size=+3>Proposed Rules</font>
<hr>

<CENTER>
The proposed rules marked with an * are of particular interest to small
business and the department specifically requests comments on those issues.
Comments on any rule are encouraged.<P>
</CENTER>
<HR>
<h3 align=center>
Illinois Register<BR>
November 22, 1996
</h3>
<hr>

<h4>DEPARTMENT OF CENTRAL MANAGEMENT SERVICES</h4>

<strong><em>Pay Plan</em></strong>- Updates hourly and daily rate changes to conform with federal minimum wage increase.  Also deletes obsolete rates.<p>

<hr>
<h4>ILLINOIS COMMUNITY COLLEGE BOARD</h4>

<strong><em>Administration of the Illinois Public Community College Act</em></strong> - Clarifies membership on the Student Advisory Board.<p>

<hr>
<h4>DEPARTMENT OF NATURAL RESOURCES</h4>

<strong><em>Falconry and the Captive Propagation of Raptors</em></strong> - Provides a framework  to discontinue sponsorship of an apprentice class permittee; specifies bag and possession limits for falconry hunting seasons; specifies apprentice class permittees may not raise raptors in captivity and can possess on passage raptors.<p>

<hr>
<h4>DEPARTMENT OF PROFESSIONAL REGULATION</h4>

<strong><em>Illinois Architecture Practice Act of 1989*</em></strong> - Applicants for an architect license in Illinois who graduated from a program outside the US or its territories and whose first language is not English must submit certification of passage of the TOEFL and TSE before taking the exam.  Persons who desire to practice in Illinois in the form of a partnership, limited liability company, corporation or sole proprietorship under an assumed name must to register with the Department  (Statutory)<p>

<hr>
<h4>ILLINOIS RACING BOARD</h4>

<strong><em>Jockeys, Apprentices, Jockey Agents, and Valets</em></strong> - Reduces the minimum suspension for careless riding from 5 to 3 days; allows for fines.<p>

<hr>
<h4>SECRETARY OF STATE</h4>

<strong><em>Public Library Construction Grants</em></strong> - Enables libraries to apply for special grants under the construction program.  (Emergency)<p>

<hr>
<h4>DEPARTMENT OF TRANSPORTATION</h4>

<strong><em>Oversize and Overweight Permit Movements on State Highways *</em></strong> - Repeals section on transmission or retransmission of permits; updates statutory and federal citations. <p>


