<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Illinois Agriculture & Vegetable Seed Permit	</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Agriculture & Vegetable Seed Permit	
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Agriculture<BR>
P.O. Box 19281<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794-9281<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
505 Illinois Compiled Statutes 110/1 et seq. (Illinois Seed Law)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A permit is required before any business may sell, process or distribute agricultural seeds, vegetable seeds, lawn seeds, and other seeds.  This permit authorizes a business to sell, offer for sale, expose for sale or transport for sale any agricultural, vegetable, or other seeds designated by the Department within Illinois.  A permit is not required for a person selling only the packaged lines which have been packed and distributed by a permit holder.  Violations are a business offense, and subject to a $1,000 fine and costs.  Permits expire
annually.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must complete and file an  "Application for Illinois Agriculture and Vegetable Seed Permit" form.  Application processing usually takes about three weeks.  If the permit is denied, the process is subject to the Administrative Review Law.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Each container of seed sold shall have a label conspicuously placed.  Each person whose name appears on the label shall keep complete records for 2 years.  Each person whose name appears on the label shall keep a file sample of each lot of seed samples for one year.  All records and samples must be accessible to Department inspectors during  business hours.  All permits must be conspicuously posted in the permit holder's place of business.  The permit holder must file an Illinois Disposition Report at the time of renewing a permit
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees: </H3>
<DL><DD>
Retail Seed Dealer			$10.00<P>
Wholesale Seed Deale		$30.00<P>
Seed Broker				$30.00<P>
Seed Merchant				$40.00<P>
Operator of Public Auction	$30.00<P>
</DD></DL>


<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
