<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: License for Livestock Dealer</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.  Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License for Livestock Dealer
</DD></DL>
<HR>

<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Agriculture<BR>
Bureau of Animal Health<BR>
P.O. Box 19281<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794-9281<BR>
(217) 782-4944<BR>
</DD></DL>
<HR>

<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
111 Illinois Compiled Statutes 401, 645/1-21.<P>
</DD></DL>
<HR>

<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A license is required to operate as a livestock dealer and/or order buyer. This license authorizes a business to buy, sell or offer to sell, exchange, barter, or negotiate the sale of cattle, goats, sheep, or swine (other than feeder swine) in Illinois.   Conducting this business without a license is a petty offense and is subject to a $200 fine.  Licenses are valid for one fiscal year or the part of that year remaining at the time of issuance. (The renewal date is April 15 each year.)<P>
</DD></DL>
<HR>

<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must complete and file an  "Application for Illinois Livestock Dealer License" (Form # LD-1), naming each partner if a partnership, or each director and officer of a corporation, the address, financial resources, and a list of all persons authorized to represent or act for it under this Act.  The licensing process usually takes about one week.<P> 

An application may be denied if the applicant is not qualified or does not meet the requirements of this Act.  Denied applications may be appealed to the Director of Agriculture and hearing  may be requested.  After that, appeal may be made to the Circuit Court.<P>
</DD></DL>
<HR>

<H3>VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites, & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must file a surety bond, a trust fund agreement, or a letter of credit with the Department.  Licensees must record each purchase, identifying the seller, date of purchase,  number and identification of animals.  All sales of female feeder cattle must be reported to the Department weekly.  Records must be maintained for a period of 3 years.  Licensee must file an annual report with the Department.<P>
</DD></DL>
<HR>

<H3>VII.  Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
An original license is $25.00;  Annual renewal fee is $10.00;  The fee for each branch office is $10.0;  The fee for each agent authorized to represent or act for a licensee is $5.00.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
