<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: License for Slaughtering and Processing Establishments</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License for Slaughtering and Processing Establishments
</DD></DL>

<HR>				
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Agriculture<BR>
Bureau of Meat & Poultry Inspection / Compliance Section<BR>
State Fairgrounds, P.O. Box 19281<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794<BR>
(217) 782-6684<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>		
<H3>III. Statute: </H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 650/1 - 20  (The Meat & Poultry Inspection Act.)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL>
This license is required for any business operating a facility where animals or poultry are slaughtered and/or processed for food for human consumption. The license authorizes the holder to cook, grind, smoke, slice and manufacture meat products for sale to other than "end" consumers.  License holders also may slaughter and custom slaughter animals and/or poultry for sale.  Doing business without a license is a Class A misdemeanor, and is subject to a fine of $1,000 and a year in  jail.  A license is valid for one year and expires on June 30 each year.
</DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The applicant must complete and file an application with the Department.  Applicants doing business under an assumed name must include proof of registration with the clerk of the county in which the business is located. Corporations must include proof  of registration  with the Secretary of State's Office.  Blueprints of the facility must be submitted to the Department for review and the facility must be inspected and approved by the Regional Administrator.  License approval usually takes about 4 to 5 weeks.  
</DD></DL>

<HR>	
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The applicant must have no prior convictions of violating the Meat & Poultry Inspection Act.  The facility must conform to the requirements of the USDA 570 Handbook.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The fee for the license is $50.00.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
