<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: 1.) Pesticide Applicator/Operator/Dealer Licenses
2.) Pesticide Product Registration
3.) Agrichemical Containment Facility Permit</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.  Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
1.) Pesticide Applicator/Operator/Dealer Licenses<P>
2.) Pesticide Product Registration<P>
3.) Agrichemical Containment Facility Permit<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Agriculture<BR>
Bureau of Environmental Programs<BR>
P.O. Box 19281<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794-9281<BR>
(217) 785-2427<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
415 Illinois Compiled Statutes 60/1-25.  (Illinois Pesticide Act.)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A license is required for pesticide manufacturers, dealers, applicators and users.  Individuals working with pesticides requiring licenses are: Certified Pesticide Applicator, Licensed Operator, and Pesticide Dealer.  These licenses authorize the sale and/or commercial application of registered pesticides.  Applicants for these licenses must pass a written examination.<P>

Registration of a product with the Department allows the product to be used in Illinois.  Individual pesticide products must be registered with the Department.  Product registrations are valid for one year.<P>

Permits are required for construction and operation of an agrichemical facility containment area. A permit allows the storage mixing, repackaging, or transfer of bulk pesticides. (The containment permit is valid for 5 years.)  Operating without a permit or use of unregistered pesticides is a Class A misdemeanor and may  result in a fine of not less than $5,000. <P>
</DD></DL> 

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<STRONG><EM>Licenses:</EM> </STRONG>Interested parties must pass an applicator/operator/dealer test before filing an application with the Department.  The Department provides training/testing clinics in cooperation with the University of Illinois.   The licensing process usually takes about 3 weeks after the Department receives an application.  The most common reasons for denial is failure to pass the test or a prior violation of the Act.

Product registration:  Applicants must complete and file Form # IL-406-0004-(8-83) with a copy of the product label.  The product must have a current registration with the U.S. EPA.

<STRONG><EM>Agrichemical Facility Containment Permit:</EM></STRONG>  Applicants must complete and file Application for Permit & Construction Approval-Agrichemical Facility, together with technical information and drawings, including a map of the facility and the surrounding area, the water supply/well protection plan, operational and management practices plan, engineering plans and specifications, the collection and recovery system flow diagram, storage facilities, and containment areas and more.  Denial of  any of these licenses, registrations, and permits, may be appealed under the terms of  the Administrative Hearing Review.<P>
</DD></DL>
<H3>VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<STRONG><EM>License:</EM></STRONG> Commercial applicator must provide a Certificate of Insurance to the Director.  The Certificate must be current and on file with the Department at all times.<P>

<STRONG><EM>Registration:</EM></STRONG>  The product must be currently registered with the U.S. EPA.<P>

<STRONG><EM>Permit:</EM></STRONG>  The facility must comply with local zoning ordinances.  Persons or businesses issued  these licenses, certificates or permits is required to keep records of information described on forms provided by the Department.  Department inspectors must be allowed access to all records during normal business hours.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.  Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Commercial applicator license is $30.<P>
Commercial operator license is $20.<P>
Pesticide dealer license is $100.<P>
Each individual or business registering a product must pay a fee of $250, plus $50 per product.<P>
There is no fee for a Containment Permit.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
