<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Registration of Buyers & Brokers of Livestock for Slaughter</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.  Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Registration of Buyers & Brokers of Livestock for Slaughter
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Agriculture<BR>
Bureau of Animal Health<BR>
P.O. Box 19281<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794-9281<BR>
(217) 782-4994<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
111 Illinois Compiled Statutes 501, 655/1-22.  (Slaughter Livestock Buyers Act.)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Buyers, packers and brokers of  livestock (cattle, goats, sheep, swine, or any other animals of the bovine, caprine, ovine, or porcine species) must register with the Department.  Registered  business may purchase livestock in Illinois for slaughter when the livestock is slaughtered for food, and to market the slaughtered meat products.  Registered brokers may buy, receive, sell, exchange, negotiate, or solicit the sale, resale, exchange, or transfer of any slaughtered livestock purchased from the producer.  Failure to register is a Class A misdemeanor.  Each day of violation constitutes a separate offense.  Registration remains in effect until canceled, suspended, or revoked.  
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must complete and file with the Department Form SL-1, (Application for Registration Under Slaughter Livestock Buyers Act).  The licensing process usually takes about one week.  The Department may refuse to issue a license if the applicant does not possess the necessary qualifications or does not meet the requirements of this Act.  If refused, the applicant may appeal to the Director of Agriculture and request a hearing.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must file a financial statement (Form SL-6) or a surety bond (Form P&SA-1) with the Department.  A certificate of registration must be prominently displayed at each place of business.  Each registrant must maintain records of each transaction.  Registrants must pay for livestock within 24 hours after purchase.   Registrants must file an annual report with the Illinois Department of Agriculture.  Registrants must allow Department inspectors to enter the business during ordinary business hours to examine records.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.  Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
