<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Medicaid Certification</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. Business Requirement Profile:</H3> 
<DL><DD>Medicaid Certification</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>II. Agency:</H3> <DL> <DD>  Illinois Department of Alcoholism & Substance Abuse<BR>
               Medicaid Certification Unit<BR>
               100 W. Randolph St.; Suite 5-600<BR>
               Chicago, IL 60601<BR>
               (312) 814-4817<BR></DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:    </H3>
<DL><DD>20 Illinois Compiled Statutes 305/4-1.</DD><BR></DL>
<H3>Regulation: </H3>
<DL><DD>77 Illinois  Administrative Code; Section 2090.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>

<DL><DD><P>This certification establishes criteria for participation by subacute alcoholism and other drug abuse treatment
programs in the Medicaid Program.

<P>Medicaid Certification allows the provider to enroll in the Illinois
Medical Assistance Program (Medicaid) as a subacute alcoholism and
substance abuse (A/SA) treatment provider. Any service provider who is not
certified cannot participate in the State's Medicaid Program.

<P>Failure to comply with the requirements of the Medical Standards Program
will result in the provider being issued a written warning or having its
certification suspended or terminated for the Illinois Medical Assistance
Program. The length of the effective term for certification is 3 years.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V. Approval Process:</H3>

<DL><DD><P> Each alcohol or substance abuse treatment provider
who wants to enroll in the Medicaid program must submit a completed
application (Form# IL-409-0189), a copy of the applicant's most recent
"utilization review report", and the most recent annual audit and financial
data. Applications that omit more than two components will be returned.
Completed applications may then be resubmitted. If a completed application
is reviewed and determined to be in compliance with the proper
requirements, the department will conduct an on-site inspection. If the on-
site inspection does not confirm compliance with the requirements, the
applicant must correct the deficiencies within 60 days, or the department
will deny certification. If certification is denied, the applicant may
appeal the decision and request a hearing.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>

<DL><DD><P>To be eligible to apply, a provider must be either:

<P>A.)  Licensed by IDASA according to the provisions of the Alcoholism &
Other Drug Abuse and Dependency Act for one or more of the following
treatment categories:

<P>Outpatient - Adult and/or adolescent outpatient; adult and/or adolescent
intensive outpatient; adult medical detoxification; or Residential - Adult
and/or adolescent residential rehabilitation, adult and/or adolescent
medical detoxification, social setting detoxification for alcoholism.
(Adult and/or adolescent day treatment and adult and/or adolescent
detoxification would be under this category).

<P>B.)  Licensed by the Illinois Department of Public Health according to the
provisions of the Hospital Licensing Act, and accredited by the Joint
Commission on Accreditation for Healthcare Organizations (JCAHO). Illinois
Department of Alcoholism & Substance Abuse Medicaid Certification.

<P>Medicaid-enrolled service providers must be recertified every three years
by the Department

<P>Ninety (90) days prior to the anniversary date of certification, the
provider must submit to the Department

<P>1.)  A "Recertification" application (Form# IL-409-0189).

<P>2.)  A statement that the provider continues to meet all requirements of
their certification.

<P>3.)  Copies of all Utilization Review reports since the date of last
certification.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees: </H3>

<DL><DD>None</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
