<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Application for a Permit to Organize a State Bank </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Application for a Permit to Organize a State Bank 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II. Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Commissioner of Banks and Trust Companies<BR>
Corporate Applications Division<BR>
310 South Michigan Avenue, Suite 2130<BR>
Chicago, IL 60604<BR>
(312) 793-2043<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
205 Illinois Compiled Statutes, 5/7-13 (Illinois Banking Act)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A permit is required to incorporate a new state-chartered bank. Applicants must be either a bank holding company or consist of 5 or more residents of the State.  Processing the permit takes about 2 to 3 months.  A permit is valid for 6 months, and can be extended. 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V. Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must complete and file with the Commissioner an "Application for a Permit to Organize".  The application must contain information including the following: The name, address, business/occupation, address of each applicant; a statement of the proposed management, including the name/location of proposed bank; amount of capital, surplus and reserve for operating expenses; number of shares, par value and amount for which each share of capital and preferred stock will be sold, and any classes of preferred stock; statement of financial worth for each applicant; three personal character references for each applicant, and other relevant information as required by the Commissioner.<P> 

Background investigations of each applicant, the proposed director and senior officers of the new bank will be conducted by the Agency.  If a permit is issued, the incorporators may proceed with stock subscription for capital stock and organization of the bank.  Upon completion of all requirements and full payment of the capital stock, surplus and reserves, the Commissioner examines the affairs of the proposed bank.<P>

If all requirements are found to be complete, a charter is issued. The bank must commence business within one year of the date of issuance or request an extension.  Applications may be denied if applicants do not have sufficient capital.  Applicants may overcome denial by fulfilling all charter requirements.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Prior to filing an "Application for a Permit to Organize", the incorporators must meet with representatives of the Commissioner.  
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The non-refundable application fee for a charter is $7,500.  Fee for a background investigation of each organizer, director and senior officer of the proposed bank  is $36.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
