<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop:  Certification to be a provider of Medicaid Community Mental Health Services.</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
 Certification to be a provider of Medicaid Community Mental Health Services.
</DD></DL> 

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Children & Family Services<BR>
406 E. Monroe, Station #60<BR>
Springfield, IL 62701<BR>
Office of Mental Health Services<BR>
(217) 785-2697<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute: </H3>

<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Title 5  Chapter I: Department of Mental Health and Developmental Disabilities; Part 132 Medicaid Community Mental Health Services Program.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Providers of therapeutic mental health services to children who are DCFS clients must be certified by the Department.<P>

Agencies seeking certification in this program must directly provide Mental Health Assessment, Individualized Treatment Plan (ITP) Development, Review and Modification and Psychiatric Treatment.<P>

Agencies providing Rehabilitative Mental Health Services must directly provide Mental Health Assessment, Individualized Treatment Plan (ITP) Development, Review and Modification, and at least one of the rehabilitative mental health services.<P>

Agencies that contract with DCFS to provide Family Intervention, Stabilization and Reunification Services must provide directly, or by subcontract, Rehabilitative Services Assessment, Rehabilitative Services Plan (RSP) Development, Review and Modification, and at least one other specified service.<P>

The ITP or RSP must be completed within forty-five (45) days of the assessment.  With the exception of Crisis Intervention Services, all additional Medicaid services must be specified in the ITP/RSP and cannot be initiated before the treatment plan has been signed.<P>

The Medicaid Mental Health Services Initiative enables the Department of Children and Family Services (DCFS) to enhance the range and quality of mental health services provided to children in the specialized substitute care system by allowing service providers across the state to increase the frequency and type of therapeutic services they provide to DCFS clients.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
An application to be certified as a provider must be filed with the Department's Office of Mental Health Services. The Department will review the application for compliance with applicable rules and matching each relevant item of the Medicaid Certification Checklist with the material submitted in the application.<P>  

Certification can be granted on the basis of this desk review, but the Department will conduct subsequent site visits to verify compliance.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must be child welfare or mental health services providers, and must contract with either DCFS or DMHDD prior to application.<P>  

Residential service providers must have the appropriate licenses from DCFS.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>


<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
