<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: License To Operate Child Care Facility</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License To Operate Child Care Facility
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Children and Family Services<BR>
Bureau of Licensure and Certification<BR>
406 East Monroe St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62701<BR>
(217) 785-2688<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes Section 10
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Title 89 Illinois Administrative Code, Sections 401-410
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A Child Care License is required to operate a home day care and day care centers child welfare agency, child care institution, group homes, etc.<P>  

The purpose of the License is to specify  minimum standards for the care of children apart from their parent or guardian.<P>  

Daycare licenses are valid for 3 years; all other types of licenses are valid for 4 years.<P>

Providing child care without a license is a Class A misdemeanor and violators are subject to fines. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must file an application for Child Care License, which are available from local offices of the Department's Bureau of Licensure and Certification.<P>

Applicants, members of the household and/or employees must authorize a search of the Child Abuse and Neglect Tracking System and a criminal history check if eighteen years of age or older.  The Department will conduct an on-site inspection of proposed child care facility; health and fire safety inspections; health clearances for caregivers and staff qualifications as required by facility type.<P>  

Applications may require up to 2-6 months to process.<P>

Applications may be denied due to criminal or child abuse or neglect history.  Denials based on criminal records are subject to Department review.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The proposed site for child care facility must be established and identified in the application.<P>

Applicant may be subject to local fire, health, zoning and other governmental requirements.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
