<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: License for Sellers of Pre-Need Funeral Contracts</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>
<H3>I. Business Requirement Profile:
</H3><dl><dd>
License for Sellers of Pre-Need Funeral Contracts
</dd></dl><hr>
<H3>II. Agency:
</H3><dl><dd>
Office of the Comptroller<BR>
Cemetery and Burial Trust Department<BR>
100 West Randolph, Suite 15-500<BR>
Chicago, Illinois 60601<BR>
(312) 814-5783<BR>
</dd></dl><hr>

<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<dl><dd>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 45/T et seq. (Illinois Funeral or Burial Funds Act)
</dd></dl><p>
<H3>Regulation:</H3><dl><dd>

77 Illinois Administrative Code, Part(s) 500.
<p></dd></dl><hr>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<dl><dd>
Sellers of pre-need funeral contracts* must be licensed by the Office of the Comptroller, whether or not the contract is funded by a trust agreement, life insurance or annuity. Licenses are valid until canceled by the licensee or revoked by the Comptroller. Individual salespersons employed by a licensee are not required to be licensed. Any person who violates this Act is guilty of a Class 4 Felony and may be subject to fines.  Duplicate licenses may be issued to
the holders of an original licensed entity for posting in the place of business. <P>

*(An agreement for furnishing or performing funeral services)<P></dd></dl><hr>

<H3>V. Approval Process:</H3>
<dl><dd>
Applicants must submit a signed and duly verified Application for  License, Funeral & Burial Funds to the State Comptroller. Applications must include the full name; business and home address for the applicant, every member, officer and director; a statement of the applicant's approximate net worth, and; a fidelity bond or an unconditional letter of credit from a bank, credit union, or trust company. Complete applications are generally processed within one week. Applications may be denied if the applicant, is not authorized to transact business in Illinois; has made false statements on the application; or, if the applicant is insolvent or fraudulent in conducting business. Before a licensee may be refused issuance or renewal or before revocation of a license, a hearing is held to determine if the applicant/licensee is entitled to licensure. A final administrative decision may be reviewed by the county circuit court. 
<p></dd></dl><hr>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites; Co-Requisites; Post-Requisites:
</H3><dl><dd>
Licensees must keep accurate records of all transactions; copies of all pre-need contracts; trust agreements, and other agreements; dates and amounts of payments made and accepted; names and addresses of the contracting parties; the persons for whose benefit such funds are accepted and the names of the depositories of such funds. If an insurance policy or tax-deferred annuity is used to fund the pre-need contract, the licensee must maintain accurate accounts, books and records of all insurance policies and tax-deferred annuities used to fund the pre-need contract; the name and address of the insured, annuitant and initial beneficiary, and; the name and address of the insurance company issuing the policy or annuity. The licensee must annually submit a report to the Comptroller. The report must be made within 75 days after the end of the licensees fiscal year. <p></dd></dl><hr>

<H3>VII. Fees:
</H3><dl><dd>
The application fee is $25. Annual Reports must be submitted with a $10 fee. All books, records and accounts of the licensee with respect to trust funds, insurance policies or tax-deferred annuities must be made available to the Comptroller. Fees for examining these books, records, and accounts is based upon the total amount of trust funds held by the license at the end of the of the calendar/fiscal year. The fee schedule is as follows:<P>
<dl>
<dt>  Less than $10,000:  <dd>                    no charge
 <dt> $10,000 or more but less than $50,000:   <dd>     $10
  <dt>$50,000 or more but less than $100,000: <dd>    $40
  <dt>$100,000 or more but less than $250,000:  <dd>    $80
  <dt>$250,000 or more:                     <dd>      $100

<p></dl></dd></dl>






<HR>
