<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Unemployment Insurance Contributions</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all><H3>
 I.  Business Requirement  Profile:
        </H3><DL><DD>
Unemployment Insurance Contributions
                     </DD></DL><HR><H3>
II.  Agency:                           </H3>
                                            <DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Employment Security          <BR>
Revenue Division<BR>
401 South State Street<BR>
Chicago, Illinois  60605  <BR>
(312) 793-4880<BR>
<P>
Regional Revenue Offices:<p>

<PRE>
1. Metro North                      2. Metro South
   527 South Wells Street              9415 S. Western Ave.
   Chicago, Illinois 60607             Chicago, Illinois  60620
   (312)793-5000                       (312)881-6860

3. Northern Region				 4. Northwest Region
   260 East Indian Trail Rd.		    410 Elm Street
   Aurora, Illinois  60505		    Peoria, Illinois  61605
   (708)844-8455				    (309)671-3160

5. Central Region 				 6. Southern Region
   555 South Pasfield       		    P. O. Box 1389
   Springfield, Illinois  62704        403 N. 42nd. St
   (217)782-2790     			    Mt. Vernon, Illinois  62864
                                       (618)242-3701
</PRE>
</DD></DL><HR><H3>

III. Statute:</H3><DL><DD>
820 Illinois Compiled Statutes 405/100-3200 (Il. Unemployment Insurance Act)
                               </DD></DL><H3>
          Regulation:</H3> <DL><DD> 56 Illinois Administrative Code 2712-2960
                          </DD>    </DL><HR><H3>
IV.  Requirement Description:</H3><DL><DD> Unemployment Insurance Contributions fund the Unemployment Insurance Trust Fund from which Unemployment Insurance benefits are paid. Businesses required to contribute include employers with:  A gross payroll of  $1,500 in a calendar quarter; one or more employees within 20 or more weeks of a calendar year, or Federal Unemployment Tax Act (FUTA) liability; agricultural entities with 10 or more workers within 20 or more weeks of a calendar year or $20,000 in cash wages in a calendar quarter; non-profit entities (as defined in paragraph 501 C-3 of the Internal Revenue Code) with four or more workers within 20 or more weeks in a calendar year; employers of  domestic workers who pay $1,000 or more in cash wages in a calendar quarter, and  governmental entities.
                                          </DD></DL><HR><H3>
V.   Approval Process:</H3><DL><DD>   Employers must complete and file with the Department Form# UI-1 ("Report to Determine Liability Under the Illinois Unemployment Insurance Act") within 30 days of commencing business operations.  Entities that meet the criteria described  above will receive a letter from the Department within 6 weeks detailing their status, rates or liability.
                                   </DD></DL><HR><H3>
VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3><DL><DD>  Employers who purchase or reorganize an existing business must undertake the "letter of clearance" procedure or inherit the unpaid debt of a predecessor employer, and must file the forms required by the Director within 120 days of the transaction.  
Employers that do not meet this requirement will not benefit from the "good" experience of their predecessor.  Employers may terminate if they fail to meet the criteria necessary for liability for one calendar year or at the end of the quarter that they cease employing workers.
                            </DD></DL><HR><H3>
VII.      Fees:
 </H3><DL><DD>
No fee is charged for the application process.  However, employers found liable for the payment of contributions are assigned either a "standard" tax rate, a rate based on their industry, their own experience or the experience of their predecessor.
              </DD></DL>



<HR>
