<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Toxic Chemical Release Reporting (Form R).</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile: </H3>

<DL><DD>Toxic Chemical Release Reporting (Form R).</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>

             <DL> <DD> Illinois Environmental Protection Agency<BR>
               Office of Chemical Safety<BR>
               2200 Churchill Rd.<BR>
               Springfield, IL 62706<BR>
               (217) 785-0830<BR></DD></DL>

<HR>          
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>

<DL><DD>415 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5/25b.  (Illinois Environmental Protection Act)</DD></DL>

<DL><DD>Section 313, 42 U.S. Code 11013.  (Emergency Planning & Community Right-to-Know-Act.)</DD></DL>

<H3>Regulation: </H3>

<DL><DD>40 Code of  Federal Regulations 372. (Toxic Chemical Release Reporting & Community Right-to-Know Act.)</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>

<DL><DD><P>A business that manufactures, imports or processes 25,000 pounds of a toxic chemical*, or uses 10,000 pounds of a
toxic chemical, a year, with 10 or more full time employees and uses SIC
codes 20 through 39 must file an annual Toxic Chemical Release Form R with
the Agency.  Businesses required to file Toxic Chemical Release Form R by
Section 313 of the federal EPCRA must also file those forms with the
Agency, disclosing information on emergency and routine releases of
specified toxic chemicals and other information on their use, storage
quantities, as well as release reduction and recycling efforts.

<P>Businesses that fail to file a Toxic Chemical Release Form R by July 1 will
be contacted by the Agency and given 30 days to comply, after which charges
will be filed and a hearing scheduled before the Pollution Control Board.

<P>*Toxic chemicals are listed in 40 CFR 372.65  (Chemicals are periodically
added or deleted from this list.  Also, USEPA is proposing to add
additional facility criteria.  Check a current Code of Federal Regulations
and the Federal Register Index or call the EPCRA Hotline at 800/535-0202.)</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>

<DL><DD>Upon receipt, the Agency will review the Toxic Chemical Release Form R and require any inaccurate, incomplete or missing information to be corrected.</DD></DL>

<HR>     
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>

<DL><DD> Annual filings of Toxic Chemical Release Form R reports are due July 1.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>

<DL><DD> None.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
