<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Consumer Installment Loan Act License</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>
<H3>I. Business Requirement Profile:
</H3><dl><dd>
Consumer Installment Loan Act License
</dd></dl><HR>
<h3>
II. Agency:
</h3><dl><dd>
Department of Financial Institutions<br>
Consumer Credit Division <br>
100 West Randolph, Suite 15-700<br>
Chicago, Illinois 60601<br>
(312) 814-5145 <br>
</dd></dl><HR>

<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<dl><dd>
205 Illinois Compiled Statutes 670/1 (Consumer Installment Loan Act)<P>
</dd></dl>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<dl><dd>
38 Illinois Administrative Code Chapter 1, Part 110 <P>
</dd></dl><hr>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:
</H3><dl><dd>
A license is required to make direct consumer loans of amounts up to $10,000. A separate license is required for each business location. Conducting business without a license is a business offense and subject to a fine from $100 to $1,000 for each offense. Violations are a Class A misdemeanor. Annual  licenses expire on December 31.<p></dd></dl><hr>

<H3>V. Approval Process:
</H3><dl><dd>
Applicants must submit a license application for the Consumer Installment Loan Act, together with a supplemental application including applicant's history and business experience, a $1,000 Surety Bond, information on an Attorney-In-Fact (an Attorney-In-Fact authorizes the Director of the Department of Financial Institutions as accepting the notice of process), a credit report, and a financial statement. Applications usually take 45 days to process. Denied applications  may be reviewed through a hearing.<p></dd></dl><hr>

<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post Requisites:  
</H3><dl>
<dt><STRONG>Post-Requisites:</STRONG><dd> Each location is examined annually and for each year thereafter the license must be renewed by no later than December 15. Each entity must complete an Annual Report on forms prescribed  by the Director of the Department of Financial Institutions.<p></dl><hr>

<H3>VII.  Fees:</H3>
<dl><dd><dl>
<dt>License Fee:  <dd>      $300 (Annual) or $150 (Semi-Annual) 
<dt>Investigation Fee: <dd> $300
<dt>Relocation Fee:  <dd>   $100 
<dt>Name Change:    <dd>    $ 25 
<dt>Annual Examination: <dd>$100 / Per Examiner, Per Day 
<p></dl></dl>







<HR>
