<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Occupational Licenses</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Occupational Licenses
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Gaming Board / Department of Revenue<BR>
Enforcement Division<BR>
160 North LaSalle St., 3rd floor<BR>
Chicago, IL 60601<BR>
(312) 814-4700<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
230 Illinois Compiled Statutes 10/1.
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Title 80  Illinois Administrative Code, Part 3000.100
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A License is required to manage gambling operations  aboard a riverboat
licensed to operate in the State of Illinois.  The Board issues licenses to
persons after determining that the applicant is or remains eligible for an
occupational license.  Licenses are valid for one year and may be renewed for qualified candidates.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Interested parties must be 21 to perform any function involving gaming by
patrons (applicants for non-gaming functions must be 18), and file an
application on forms available from the Board, stating whether he or she
has been issued prior gambling related licenses, has been licensed in
another state, whether that license or permit has been suspended,
restricted or revoked, and if so, for what period of time.<P>

Applicants must provide two sets of fingerprints and a Personal Disclosure
Form 1 (for Owner, Management), Form 2 (for Supervisory, Dealer,
Surveillance, Security, Slot Technician, Slot Shift Manager, Slot
Attendant), or Form 3 (for Count, Credit, Accounting, Food & Beverage,
Change Attendant, Boat Operations, Administration, Support Personnel, Non-
Gaming) depending upon which employment position the applicant is applying
for.<P>

The applicant is then issued a temporary license allowing him/her to be
actively employed at the riverboat.  Background investigations are
conducted by the Board.  Processing time for applications varies depending
on the extent of the background investigation required.  Reasons for denial
may include conduct considered in violation of the Act and rules
established by the Board.  If  denied, the applicant may request a hearing.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<PRE>
Form 1 Application Fee:       $1,000<P>
Form 2 Application Fee:       $  250<P>
Form 3 Application Fee:       $   75<P>
Annual License Renewal Fee:   $   50<P>
</PRE>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
