<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Archaeological and Paleontological Resources Protection Act</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.  Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Archaeological and Paleontological Resources Protection Act
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Historic Preservation Agency<BR>
Division of Preservation Services<BR>
Old State Capitol<BR>
Springfield, IL 62701<BR>
(217) 785-5027<BR> 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
20 Illinois Compiled Statutes 3435
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The purpose of this Act is to protect resources of Archeological or Paleontological  significance located on public land.  A permit is required to excavate or otherwise disturb archaeological or paleontological sites on any public land  (for example, park districts, school districts, county facilities, etc.). A developer undertaking any project on publicly owned land containing Paleontological or Archaelogical resources must obtain the approval of the Agency. Failure to comply with this Act may result in criminal sanctions.
<DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Developers undertaking projects that would disturb archaeological or paleontological sites on public lands must file a written application with the Agency describing the proposed project and requesting permission to proceed. The Agency will issue approve or deny the request within 30 days of receipt.  A permit will be issued to when the applicant has demonstrated a need for the excavation or disturbance, and sufficient and qualified personnel are avaialble to identify and evaluate any archaeological or paleontological resources, and a plan for analysis and curation of the resources. 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.  Pre-requisites, Co-requisites & Post-requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The public body owning the property must give consent.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.   Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

