<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Accident reporting requirements of the Workers' Compensation Act</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>Accident reporting requirements of the Workers' Compensation Act</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II. Agency:  </H3>
<DL><DD>Illinois Industrial Commission<BR>
               100 W. Randolph<BR>
               Chicago, IL 60601<BR>   
               Phone:  (312) 814-6500</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute Citation:</H3>
<DL><DD>820 Illinois Compiled Statutes 305/6(b).</DD></DL>

<H3>Regulation Citation:</H3>

<DL><DD> 50 Illinois Administrative Code 7010.10.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>

<DL><DD><P>Employers subject to the Workers' Compensation Act must report to the
Commission all accidental deaths, and injuries and illnesses arising out of
(or in the course of) employment, if they result in the loss of more than 3
scheduled work days.

<P>In the case of an accidental death, the report must be made within 2
working days.

<P>In all other cases, the report must be made between the 15th and 25th of
each month.

<P>If  an injury  results in permanent disability, an additional report must
be made as soon as it is determined that permanent disability resulted (or
will result) from the injury.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V. Approval Process:</H3>

<DL><DD>Reports must be filed with the Commission.  All reports are confidential by
law, but are used (only) to compile aggregate statistics.  Failure of an
employer to file these reports is a petty offense.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post Requisites:</H3>

<DL><DD>Reports are to be filed on forms provided by the Industrial Commission.</DD></DL>

<DL><DD><H3>Accident reports:</H3>
<DL><DD>IIC Form 45.</DD></DL>

<H3>Supplemental reports:</H3>
<DL><DD>IIC Form 85</DD></DL></DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>

<DL><DD>None</DD></DL>


<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
