<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Illinois Industrial Home Work Law  </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Industrial Home Work Law  
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Labor<BR>
Fair Labor Standards Division<BR>
60 N. LaSalle<BR>
Chicago, IL 60601<BR>
(312) 793-2804<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
820 Illinois Compiled Statutes 240/1 et seq.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
This law regulates the employment in  the homes of workers who manufacture, finish, repair, prepare or handle materials furnished by an employer (except articles processed only for the consumption, wearing or use of persons residing in the home). <P>

Employers of one or more Industrial Home Workers must have a current Employer's Permit. Any person who wants to perform work as an Industrial Home Worker*  must have a current Certificate issued by the Department.  Certificates will not be issued to persons with an infectious, contagious or communicable disease or who is under the age of 16. Permits and Certificates are valid  for one year.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The Department issues and renews an Employer's Permit upon receipt of a completed application and payment of applicable fees. An Employee Certificate isissued upon receipt of a completed application.  <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Employer must complete and return to the Department, records of the names and current address of workers. Employers must keep current records regarding changes in worker's employment status. Permits and certificates must be renewed annually.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Employer's Permit application fee is $200.00. Renewal fees range between $50 and $200, depending upon the number of workers he or she employs. There is no fee for a Home Worker's Certificate.<P>

*("industrial home work" means processing in a home, any article(s), the material for which is furnished by an employer, except articles processed only for consumption, wearing or use of persons who live in the home where the work is performed)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
