<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Personnel Records Review Act</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Personnel Records Review Act
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Labor<BR>
Fair Labor Standards Division<BR>
160 N. LaSalle<BR>
Chicago, IL 60601<BR>
(312) 793-1805<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
820 Illinois Compiled Statutes 40/0.01-13
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV:	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The Act establishes the employee's right to review, copy and correct personnel records, and proscribes how  an employer may gather and use information contained in those files. The purpose of the Act is to minimize the possibility that an employer would effect staffing, disciplinary, promotion and advancement decisions in an arbitrary and capricious manner.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
An aggrieved employee may file a complaint with the Department, alleging that his or her rights have been denied under the Act.  The Act authorizes the Department to investigate the complaint and to "attempt to resolve the complaint by conference, conciliation, or persuasion."  The Department may compel an employer's compliance with the Act by a civil action.  An aggrieved employee may file a private suit against his or her employer upon receipt of notice that the Department has concluded its enforcement efforts and will take no further action on the matter. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
