<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: School Visitation Rights Act    </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
School Visitation Rights Act    
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Labor<BR>
Fair Labor Standards Division<BR>
160 N. LaSalle<BR>
Chicago, IL 60601<BR>
(312) 793-2804<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
820 Illinois Compiled Statutes 147/1
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
This Act permits employed parents and guardians time away from the job for employees to attend necessary educational or behavioral conferences at the schools their children attend.  The Act applies to both public and private employers of 50 or more workers.  The provision is contingent upon the employee working for the employer six months prior to the requested leave, and working more than half the average number of hours for full-time equivalent status.  No requirement for payment of the hours is provided, but employers are encouraged to allow employees to make-up the leave time.<P>

Employees must be allowed to attend school conferences or activities in increments not to exceed four hours per leave or a total of 8 hours per year.  An employer may deny the leave if more than 5 % of the employer's work force is seeking school visitation leave at the same time.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Employers may require verification of attendance from the school.<P>

All schools must provide the attending parent or guardian with the information required to satisfy his or her employer of the employee's attendance, including date, time, and school official's signature. Employees must request leave prior to usage and must have exhausted all personal and vacation leave before he or she will be eligible for School Visitation leave.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
