<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Toxic Substances Disclosure to Employee Act </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Toxic Substances Disclosure to Employee Act 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Labor<BR>
Safety Inspection and Education<BR>
1 West Old State Capitol Plaza<BR>
Room 300<BR>
Springfield, IL 62701<BR>
(217) 782-9386<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
820 Illinois Compiled Statutes 255 (Toxic Substances Disclosure to Employees Act)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
56 Illinois Administrative Code 205. 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Businesses with five or more full-time employees, or a total of 20 full time and/or part-time employees, must file with the Department a list of Material Safety Data Sheets (MSDS), describing the toxic substances on the worksite. Manufacturers, Suppliersor Importers (MSI) of toxic substances, or products containing toxic substances, must file withthe Department a MSDS for each toxic substance used, produced or stored in the workplace to which employees may be exposed.  (A federal Occupational Safety and Health Administration "Form 174 - Material Safety Data Sheet" may be used for this purpose.)  Employers also must file an emergency plan with the local fire department. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
There are no required forms. However, the Department does provide a free "compliance kit" containing step-by-step instructions and forms to assist with compliance.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Employers must provide the Department with an annual update to keep this information current.  Businesses are required to comply with the provisions of 29, Code of Federal Regulations, 1910.1200. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>


<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
