<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Commercial Fishing License and Commercial Musseling License</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>
<H3> I.   Business Requirement Profile:
</H3><DL><DD>Commercial Fishing License and Commercial Musseling License
             </DD></DL><HR><H3>
II.  Agency:  </H3><DL><DD>   Illinois Department of Natural Resources<BR>
               Conservation Division<BR>
               Commercial License/Permit<BR>
               524 S. 2nd Street, Room 210  <BR>
               P. O. Box 19458                  <BR>
               Springfield, IL 62794                <BR>
               (217) 785-3423                           <BR>
</DD></DL><HR><H3>
III. Statute:</H3><DL><DD>    515 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5/15-5 to 150.
                          </DD></DL><H3>
     Regulation:</H3><DL><DD> 17 Illinois Administrative Code 830.
                             </DD></DL><HR><H3>
IV.  Requirement Description: </H3><DL><DD>License is required for any individual to engage in commercial fishing or commercial musseling in Illinois rivers, lakes and streams open to commercial fishing and musseling.  Licenses specify the limits on sizes and varieties of fish, the seasons they may be taken, the gear and equipment that may be used in commercial fishing and musseling and limitations on the operation of such gear and equipment.

Commercial fishing and musseling licenses are issued for a period of  up to one year and are valid from April 1 on the year of issue and expire with the following March 31.
                                           </DD></DL><HR><H3>
V.   Approval Process: </H3><DL><DD> License will be issued upon receipt of a completed application together with requisite fees by the Illinois Department of Natural Resources, Conservation Division, Department of License and Registration. (Most frequent reasons for denial are applicant's failure to sign the application or enter date of birth.)
                                    </DD></DL><HR><H3>
VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post Requisites: </H3><DL><DD>  Requirements for Resident Commercial Fishing or Commercial Musseling license are:<P> 
 <OL>
<LI> Applicant must have actually resided in Illinois for minimum of one year prior to application.
    <P>
<LI> Applicant must not have claimed residency in another state for a commercial fishing license.
    <P></OL></DD></DL><HR><H3>
VII. Fees:                    </H3>
                                   <DL><DD>
Commercial Fishing License:        $35 residents.<BR>
Commercial Fishing License:        $150 non-residents.<BR>
Commercial Musseling License:      $50 residents, (Resident only).  <BR>
                                                                        <P>
Make checks or money orders payable to the Department of Natural Resources.
</DD></DL>







