<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Commercial License / Permit Application</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Commercial License / Permit Application
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Natural Resources<BR>
Conservation Division, Commercial License/Permit Unit<BR>
524 S. 2nd Street, Room 210<BR>
P. O. Box 19458<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794-9458<BR>
(217) 785-3423<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A license or permit is required before an individual may engage in the following business operations:<P>

<PRE>
License/Permit:               Annual  Exp     Illinois Compiled Statute /
                                Fee   Date    Illinois Administrataive Code

Taxidermist                    $ 25  Jan. 31   515 ILCS 5/3.21, 5/20-85.
Processed Wild Game Dealer     $ 25  March 31  520 ILCS 5/3.24.
Fur Tanner                     $ 25  March 31  520 ILCS 5/3.14, 16.
Retail, Fur Buyer/Resident     $ 25  March 31  520 ILCS 5/3.12, 14, 19 & 20
Wholesale Fur Buyer/Resident   $125  March 31  520 ILCS 5/3.11, 14, 19 & 20
Fur Dealer/Non-Resident        $250  March 31  520 ILCS 5/3.14, 18, 19 & 20
Ginseng Grower                 $ 25  March 31  525 ILCS 20-2b.
Ginseng Dealer/Resident        $ 50  March 31  525 ILCS 20/2c.
Ginseng Dealer/Non-Resident    $100  March 31  525 ILCS 20/2c.
*Retail Fish Dealer/Resident   $ 10  Jan. 31   515 ILCS 5/20-70.
*Wholesale Fish Dealer/Resident $50  Jan. 31   515 ILCS 5/20-70.
*Fish Dealer/Non-Resident      $100  Jan. 31   515 ILCS 5/20-70.
Retail Minnow Dealer/Resident  $  5  Jan. 31   515 ILCS 5/20-80.
Wholesale Minnow Dealer/Resident $25 Jan. 31   515 ILCS 5/20-80.
Interstate Minnow Dealer       $500  Jan. 31   515 ILCS 5/20-80.
Mussel Dealer/Resident         $300  Jan. 31   515 ILCS 5/20-75.
Mussel Dealer/Non-Resident     $2500 Jan. 31   515 ILCS 5/20-75.
Commercial Musseling            $50  Aug. 31   515 ILCS 5/15-5 to 150/
                                               17  IAC 850.
Commercial Fishing/Resident     $35  March 31  515 ILCS 5/15-5 to 150/
                                               17  IAC 850.
Commercial Fishing/Non-Resident $150 March 31  515 ILCS 5/20-20.
</PRE>

(*If the license is for a truck, a separate license is required for each
truck.)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicant must complete, sign and submit to the
Department a "Commercial License/Permit Application", together with
appropriate fees. A single application form may be used for any or all of
the permits or licenses listed above. Applicants must swear that the
information on their applications is true and correct. (False or deceptive
information may subject applicant to arrest and revocation of license
privileges for up to five years.) Licenses and permits are issued usually
within one week after applications and fees are received by the Department,
and are valid only for the location described on the application (unless
the license is for a truck). The most common reasons for denial is
applicant's failure to sign the application.  Applications also may be
denied if the applicant's previous license was revoked or if applicant has
been cited for violations of the law.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.   Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A Fur Buyer's license requires an annual report to the Department of fur purchases made
during the year.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
See IV above.<P>

Make check or money order payable to Department of Natural Resources.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
