<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Permit to Install a Vacuum Pump on an Oil Well </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.  	Business Requirement Profile:
<DL><DD></H3>
Permit to Install a Vacuum Pump on an Oil Well 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Natural Resources<BR>
Office of Mines & Minerals<BR>
Oil & Gas Division<BR>
524 South Second Street<BR>
Springfield, IL 62701-1787<BR>
(217) 782-7756<BR>
TDD:  (217) 525-4626<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 725/6
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
62 Illinois Administrative Code 240 J
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A Permit is required to install or use a vacuum pump on an oil well. The permit remains in effect until the well is plugged. <P>

The purpose of the Permit is to protect the correlative rights of surrounding operators from any resulting oil drainage.   <P>

Failure to obtain a permit may result in enforcement action by the Department of Natural Resources, including civil penalties.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must submit an "Application for Vacuum Permit" form #OG-14, to the Office of Mines & Minerals (OMM), and proof of notice (certified mail to area producers with return receipt requested) to surrounding oil producers of intent to install a vacuum pump. <P>

If an objection is received, OMM may hold a hearing to resolve the objection. If no objection is received, the permit is issued. Review, approval and permit issuance generally takes 3 to 5 days from the receipt of the application. <P>

DNR decisions are subject to administrative review. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The well must be first have a Permit to be an oil or gas production well. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
