<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Approval of Qualified, Non-Department (Radiation) Inspectors.</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Approval of Qualified, Non-Department (Radiation) Inspectors.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Nuclear Safety<BR>
Office of Radiation Safety / Division of Electronic Products<BR>
1035 Outer Park Dr.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62704<BR>
(217) 785-9968<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
420 Illinois Compiled Statutes 40/1 - 40/44.<BR>
Radiation Protection Act of 1990.
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
32 Illinois Administrative Code, Part 410.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
In lieu of inspections by the Department, operators of radiation
installations may elect to use the services of a non-department qualified
inspector.  Individuals who conduct inspections as a qualified non-
department inspector are required to register with the Department and pay
an annual registration fee.  Anyone acting as a qualified non-department
inspector without registering with the Department, is guilty of a Class A
misdemeanor.  Approval of non-department inspectors will remain valid,
provided they continue to register annually.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants who want to be registered as a qualified non-department
inspector must complete and file Form # IL-473-0226, available from the
Department.  Applications must include evidence that the applicant has met
all education and experience requirements.  Applicants should anticipate 10
working days to process the application.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<STRONG><EM>Application Fee:</EM></STRONG>    $50<P>
<STRONG><EM>Annual Registration:</EM></STRONG>    $50
</DD></DL>



<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
