<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Licensure of entities to Possess, Use, Store, Manufacture or Distribute
Radioactive Material.</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Licensure of entities to Possess, Use, Store, Manufacture or Distribute
Radioactive Material.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Nuclear Safety<BR>
Office of Radiation Safety / Division of Radioactive Materials<BR>
1035 Outer Park Dr.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62704<BR>
(217) 785-9947<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
420 Illinois Compiled Statutes 30/0.01- 30/8, and  40/1- 40/44.
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Title 32, Illinois Administrative Code, Chapter II.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Any entity using radioactive material in Illinois must be licensed or
registered with the Department.  (Certain small sources or quantities of
radioactive material, such as those found in home smoke detectors or
luminous dial watches, are exempt.  Other small quantities, such as some
gauging devices, only need to be registered.)  Businesses that want to use
radioactive material that is not exempt, or quantities and forms other than
those requiring registration, must obtain a Radioactive Materials License.<P>

Typically, Licenses are required for medical use, research, and
manufacturing of items containing radioactive material.  Entities using
measuring and gauging devices (moisture/density gauges, lead paint gauges,
etc.) must also obtain a Radioactive Materials License prior to receiving
and using them.   Anyone may contact the Department to determine if a
license is required for a particular use. Using radioactive material
without a license is a Class B misdemeanor.  Licenses are valid for 5
years.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants for a Radioactive Materials License must file an application.
The Division of Radioactive Materials will provide assistance in preparing
a license application.<P>

Applicants must describe the type and quantities of radioactive material to
be used and the procedures to be followed for the safe receipt, use,
storage and disposal of radioactive material.<P>

If the Department review determines that the proposed program of radiation
safety is adequate to protect public and worker health and safety, a
license will be issued in 30 to 90 days.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License holders  may be inspected periodically to ensure the requirements,
regulations & conditions of the license are being met. Licensees also must
comply with regulations concerning accreditation of technologists for
medical use of radioactive materials and certification of industrial
radiographers.  Licensees may also be subject to low-level radioactive
waste reporting requirements.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The various fees associated with licensure are specified in Title 32,
Illinois Administrative Code, Part 331.  They cover the cost of routine
licensing and inspection activities performed by the Department and vary
according to the degree of complexity of the license. Licensees and
applicants for a radioactive materials license can contact the Division of
Radioactive Materials for detailed and specific information regarding fees
for a particular use of radioactive material.  There also are fees
associated with Technologist accreditation, Industrial Radiographer
certification and generation of low-level radioactive waste.
</DD></DL>


<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
