<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Registration & Inspection of Entities Using Radiation Machines.</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Registration & Inspection of Entities Using Radiation Machines.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Nuclear Safety<BR>
Office of Radiation Safety / Division of Electronic Products<BR>
1035 Outer Park Dr.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62704<BR>
(217) 785-9968<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
420 Illinois Compiled Statutes 30/0.01-30/8  and  40/1-40/44.
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
32 Illinois Administration Code: Chapter II.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
All individuals using x-ray equipment or other types of radiation producing
machines in Illinois need to be registered with the Department.  Anyone who
operates radiation machines without being properly registered is guilty of
a Class B misdemeanor.  Registration is valid for one year.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants for Registration may simply contact the Department.  When a
certificate of registration is issued, the person or entity registered is
required to use the machine in accordance with the Department's
regulations.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Registrants must also comply with other sections of the regulations
concerning accreditation of technologists who perform medical procedures,
and certification of Industrial Radiographers.  A Department inspection
must be performed within six (6) months after equipment is installed.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
All applicable registration and inspection fees will be billed by the
Department. These will consist of:<P>

<STRONG><EM>Annual Registration Fee:</EM></STRONG>  $10 per Radiation Machine Departmental Inspection<P> 
<STRONG><EM>Fees:</EM></STRONG>
<DL><DD>
a.)  $55 per Radiation Machine located in dental, veterinary, or podiatric
offices. (5-year inspection interval).<P>

b.)  $80 per Radiation Machine for all other uses. (Inspection interval
dependent on type of use and can vary from 1 to 5 years)<P>
</DL></DD>
<STRONG><EM>Non-Departmental Inspection Fees:</EM></STRONG>  Inspection costs vary, depending upon
individual arrangements.  However, the Department will assess a $25 per
radiation machine filing fee for each report.
</DD></DL>


<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
