<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Funeral Director, Embalmer and Trainee Licenses</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement  Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Funeral Director, Embalmer and Trainee Licenses
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
Licensing & Testing Division / Professional Services Section<BR>
320 West Washington<BR>
Springfield, IL 62786<BR>
(217) 785-0894<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Revised Statutes 41, Article 10.
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Title 68 Illinois Administrative Code, Chapter VII, Subchapter b, Part 1250
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Funeral Directors and embalmers must be licensed.  The purpose of licensing is to assure the public that qualified persons practice funeral directing and embalming.<P>

Practicing without a license is a Class A misdemeanor for the first offense, and a Class 4 felony for each subsequent offense. <P>

Licenses are valid for 2 years and may be renewed.  Trainee licenses may be renewed only twice.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must file a completed application with requisite fees with the Department.  Applicants must pass an exam that may include both practical demonstrations and written and oral tests and embrace the subjects of anatomy, sanitary science, health regulations. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants for a Funeral Director and Embalmer License or a Trainee License  must be at least 18, completed one year in college, a one year course teaching the practice of funeral directing and embalming, and have knowledge of measures for the prevention of and spread of disease.<P>

<EM>Additional License Qualifications: </EM> Applicants must have studied funeral directing and embalming in Illinois for one year under a licensed funeral director and embalmer, and pass the examination.<P>

<EM>Additional Trainee License Qualifications:</EM>  Applicants must have been accepted for training in funeral directing and embalming by an Illinois licensed funeral director and embalmer.<P>

Licensed practitioners must have a fixed place of practice devoted to the care and preparation for burial or for transportation of deceased human bodies.<P>

Each license holder must provide to the Department proof of completing at least 12 hours of continuing education during the 24 months preceding the expiration date of the license. <P>

Licenses must be displayed in their place of practice.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<EM>Funeral Director/Embalmer License Fees:</EM><P>
<DL><DD>
	Licensure:				$100<BR>
	Renewal          			$100<BR>
	Endorsement/Reciprocity Fee	$200<BR>
	Reinstatement: 			$ 10 plus all lapsed renewal fees<BR>
	Duplicate License Fee		$ 10<P>
</DD></DL>
<EM>Trainee Funeral Director/Embalmer License Fees:</EM><P>
<DL><DD>
	License:			$ 50<BR>
	Renewal:			$100<BR>
	Duplicate License:	$ 10<BR>
</DD></DL>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
