<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Interior Designer Registration</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Interior Designer Registration
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
Licensing & Testing Division / Professional Services Section<BR>
320 West Washington<BR>
Springfield, IL 62786<BR>
(217) 785-0894<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 310.
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
68 Illinois Administrative Code,  Chapter VII, Subchapter b, Part 1255
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Anyone holding him or herself out to the public as an interior designer, or using the title "interior designer" must be registered with the Department.  Using the title "interior designer" without Registering is a Class A misdemeanor for the first offense and a Class 4 felony for each subsequent offense.  Licenses are valid for two years.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Each applicant for registration must complete and file with the Department an application and pass a written exam.<P>

Common reasons for denying applications for Registration include:  providing false information on applications, prior conviction of a felony, failing of the examination.<P>

Appeals may be made to the Board of Interior Design Professionals, and a requested.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Before Registration, an applicant must provide evidence that he or she:<P>
<DL><DD>
1) is a graduate of a 4 or 5 year interior design program and has completed at least 2 years of full-time diversified interior design experience, or a 3 year curriculum and has 3 years of experience in the field, or a 2 year program with 4 years of experience;<P>

2)  holds a high school diploma or GED and has completed 5 years of full-time diversified interior design experience.<P>
</DD></DL>
Applicants for renewal of Registration must file an application at least one month prior to the expiration date of their current license, together with the applicable fee.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Registration Fee			$100<P> 
Renewal Fee				$160<P>
Endorsement / Reciprocity Fee	$100<P>
Reinstatement Fee			$ 20 plus all lapsed renewal fees<P>
Duplicate Certification Fee	$ 20<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
