<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Landscape Architect Registration</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Landscape Architect Registration
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
Licensing & Testing Division / Professional Services Section<BR>
320 West Washington<BR>
Springfield, IL 62786<BR>
(217) 785-0894<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 315.
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
68 Illinois Administrative Code, Chapter VII, Subchapter b, Part 1275
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:	</H3>
<DL><DD>
Anyone wishing to represent himself or herself as a landscape architect or use the title "Landscape Architect" must register with the Department.  The purpose of the registration process is to assure properly qualified landscape architects in the State of Illinois.  Holding one's self out as a Landscape Architect without  registration is a Class A misdemeanor for the first offense, and subsequent offenses are Class 4 felonies.<P>

Registration remains effective for two years.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applications for initial registration must show satisfactory demonstrate that applicant has earned an approved professional degree in landscape architecture or have adequate other education or experience required by the Department.  If an applicant appears qualified, applicant must pass an exam on specific technical and professional subjects.  If the applicant passes the examination and has complied with all other provisions of the Act, a certificate of registration will be issued.<P>

Common reasons for denying registration include:  providing false information on application forms, prior conviction of a felony, failing the examination, professional incompetence etc.<P>

Appeals are made to the Illinois Landscape Architect Registration Board, and a hearing can be requested. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
All applicants for landscape architect must have obtained a diploma or completion certificate for an accredited program in landscape architecture, together with 2 years of experience in the field.<P>

Every landscape architect must maintain a current address with the Department.<P>

An applicant who holds a registration in another state which has equivalent requirements as the State of Illinois, may be exempt from the written examination.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Registration Fee			$100<P>
Registration Renewal Fee		$200<P>
Endorsement / Reciprocity Fee	$100<P>
Reinstatement Fee			$  40 plus all lapsed renewal fees<P>
Duplicate Certification Fee		$  20<P>
</DD></DL>


<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
