<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: License for Boxing/Wrestling Promoters, Referee, Judge, Manager, Trainer, and Timekeepers<BR>
Permit for Boxing/Wrestling Promoters</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. 	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License for Boxing/Wrestling Promoters, Referee, Judge, Manager, Trainer, and Timekeepers<BR>
Permit for Boxing/Wrestling Promoters
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
100 W. Randolph, Suite 9-300<BR>
Chicago, IL 60601<BR>
312/814-4539<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 105/1-26 Professional Boxing and Wrestling Act
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Title 68 Illinois Administrative Code 1370
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A License is required to conduct business as a Boxing Promoter, Referee, Judge, Manager, Trainer, or Timekeeper in an organized, professional match.  The Department issues a separate license for each category.  Acting without a License is a Class A misdemeanor for the first offense, and Class 4 felony for each subsequent offense. <P>

Promoters must obtain a Permit from the Department at least 10 days prior to a boxing match or wrestling exhibition. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V. 	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must be of good moral character and provide a sworn statement that they are not in violation of State or federal laws or rules governing boxing/wrestling, and have had satisfactory experience in the field, and proof of participation in medical seminars pertaining to boxing/wrestling.<P>

Permits require a verified application accompanied by information including the names of promoter,  contestants and seconds, the matchmaker, the time and location of the event, seating capacity of the building where the event will occur, admission charge, amount of compensation to be paid to each participant.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<EM>Promoters must provide: </EM>A bond of at least $5,000 with the State Treasurer, proof of insurance of not less than $5,000 for each contestant, proof of security  measurers and medical supervision to protect the health and safety of the public and contestants during the event.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. 	Fees: </H3>
<DL><DD>
	Wrestling/Boxing Promoter:  	$300.<P>
	Referee 	 				$100.<P>
	Judge					$ 10.<P>
	Trainer	 (Second)			$ 10.<P>
	Timekeeper				$ 50.<P>
	Event Permit				$ 25.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
