<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: License for Detection of Deception Examiner & Registration for Detection of Deception Examiner Intern</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. 	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License for Detection of Deception Examiner & Registration for Detection of Deception Examiner Intern
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II. 	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
Licensing & Testing Division<BR>
Professional Services Section, Design Unit<BR>
320 West Washington, 3rd Floor<BR>
Springfield, Illinois 62786<BR>
Phone (217) 785-0877<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 430/1-32
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
68 Illinois Administrative Code Chapter VII, subchapter b, Part 1230
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Anyone holding themselves out to administer, or who does administer detection of deception examinations must obtain a license from the Department. <P>

Applicants must complete a six month training course, approved by the Department, under the direct supervision and control of a licensed examiner in the use of detection of deception equipment.  Registered persons will be designated as Detection of Deception Examiner. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V. 	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Application forms are available from Department by written request or by calling the Forms Unit at (217) 785-0842.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must possess a four year baccalaureate degree from an accredited institution and pass a written examination approved by the Department. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Application fee is $25 (in addition to any examination fees). <P>

Renewal fee: $180 for two years.<P>

There is no fee for registering for Detection of Deception Examiner Intern.<P>
</DD></DL>

