<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: License for Marriage & Family Therapist and Marriage & Family Therapist Continuing Education Sponsor</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. 	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License for Marriage & Family Therapist and Marriage & Family Therapist Continuing Education Sponsor
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II. 	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
Licensing & Testing Division<BR>
Health Professional Services Section<BR>
320 West Washington, 3rd Floor<BR>
Springfield, Illinois 62786<BR>
(217) 524-7540<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 55/1-170
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
68 Illinois Administrative Code,Chapter VII, Subchapter b, Part 1283
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Persons offering services to use psychotherapeutic methods to treat interpersonal and intrapersonal conflicts in the context of an individual's marital and family relationships must obtain a license from the Department. This requirement applies to all persons charging a fee to members of the public for therapy services. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must file a license application from the Department.<P>

Applicants for Marriage & Family Therapist must have a Doctoral or Masters degree in marriage and family therapy, or a related field with an equivalent course of study in marriage and family therapy, from an accredited educational institution.<P>

Applicants must have 2 years of experience in the practice of marriage and family therapy including at least 1,000 hours of face-to-face contact with couples and families for evaluation and treatment. In addition, applicants must have completed at least 200 hours of supervision of marriage and family therapy.<P>

All applicants must pass a written examination approved by the Department.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants for Marriage & Family Therapist must be 21, and U.S. citizens.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees: </H3>
<DL><DD>
Marriage & Family Therapist License:  $100<P>
Renewal: $120<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
