<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: License for Physician's Assistant in Medicine</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. 	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License for Physician's Assistant in Medicine
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II. 	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
Licensing & Testing Division<BR>
Medical Services Section<BR>
320 West Washington, 3rd Floor<BR>
Springfield, Illinois 62786	<BR>
(217) 524-7530<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 95/1-24
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Any person assisting a physician with the practice of medicine must be licensed.<P>

(Physician assistants perform a variety of tasks within a medical care specialty. All functions performed by a physician assistant are carried out under the direction and control of an appointed supervising physician.) <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Application for the license may be made after the candidate has passed an examination administered by the National Commission of on the Certification of Physician Assistants.  Interested parties should contact the Department to request an application. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The Department will evaluate candidates with regard to behavior that may be considered dishonorable, unethical or unprofessional and likely to deceive, defraud or harm the public.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees: </H3>
<DL><DD>
Physician Assistant License:		$50.<P>
Renewal: 						$80.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
