<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Licenses for Professions Subject to the Controlled Substances Act</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. 	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Licenses for Professions Subject to the Controlled Substances Act
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
Licensing & Testing Division<BR>
Health Services Section<BR>
320 West Washington, 3rd Floor<BR>
Springfield, Illinois 62786	<BR>
Phone  (217) 524-7540<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
720 Illinois Compiled Statutes 570 
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
68 Illinois Administrative Code, Chapter VII, subchapter b, Part 3100
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Persons who, in the course of their professional practice,  manufacture, distribute or dispense substances deemed as "Controlled" in the Illinois Controlled Substances Act, must obtain proper registration from the Illinois Department of  Professional Regulation. <P>

Professions having need for this license are; Physicians, Podiatric Physicians, Surgeons, Pharmacies (all divisions), and Veterinarians, and drug manufacturers and distributors.<P>

All licenses (except Physician/Surgeon) are valid for two years and may be renewed. <P>

Physician/Surgeon licenses are valid for three years and may be renewed.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V. 	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Application forms are available from the Department
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Physicians, Podiatric Physicians, Veterinarians, Pharmacies, and Dentists must obtain the Controlled Substance license in addition to all other required licenses for those professions. 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<EM>Podiatrist</EM>		$5.00 for new application and $10.00 for renewal<P>
<EM>Dentist</EM>			$5.00 for new application and $10.00 for renewal<P>
<EM>Dental Specialist</EM>	$5.00 for new application and $10.00 for renewal<P>
<EM>Physician/Surgeon</EM>	$5.00 for new application and $15.00 for renewal<P>
<EM>Pharmacies</EM>		$5.00 for new application and $10.00 for renewal<P>
<EM>Veterinarian</EM>		$5.00 for new application and $10.00 for renewal<P>
<EM>Manufacturers	</EM>	$50.00 for new application and $100.00 for renewal<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
