<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: License for Public Accountant, Public Accountant Partnership, Public Accountant Corporation & Registration for Continuing Education Sponsor  </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>
<H3>I.    Business Requirement Profile: </H3><DL><DD>License for Public Accountant, Public Accountant Partnership, Public Accountant Corporation & Registration for Continuing Education Sponsor  
                                                     </DD></DL><HR><H3>
II.  Agency:   </H3><DL><DD>Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
               Licensing & Testing Division<BR>
               Professional Services Section   <BR>
               (217) 785-0894                      <BR></DD></DL><HR><H3>

III. Statute:  </H3><DL><DD>225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 450/1-32
                            </DD></DL><H3>
     Regulation:</H3><DL><DD>      68 Illinois Administrative Code, Chapter VII, Subchapter b, Part 1420 & 1430.
                             </DD></DL><HR> <H3>
IV.  Requirement Description:</H3> <DL><DD>Any person, partnership, limited liability company or corporation desiring to practice public accounting in this state must obtain a license from the Department. The Department issues separate licenses for individuals and partnerships.
                                  </DD></DL><HR><H3>
V.   Approval Process: </H3><DL><DD>Applicants must be Certified Public Accountants (CPA) by the University of Illinois' Board of Examiners before applying. Once the Board has granted CPA status to an accountant, application can be made to the Department for a Public Accountant License. 

The Board will grant a license to persons who have received certificates as certified public accountants with one year's experience either as a staff member of a practicing public accountant or as an auditor including duties which the Illinois Public Accountants Registration Committee determines to be substantial experience. 
                                    </DD></DL><HR><H3>
VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3><DL><DD> All partnerships, limited liability companies or corporations engaged in the practice of public accounting in this State must have at least one partner, member of a limited liability company, or shareholder of a corporation licensed as a Public Accountant by the Department.  
                                                                  
Each partner, member of a limited liability company, or shareholder of a corporation personally engaged in the practice of public accounting must also be licensed as a Public Accountant. 

Each person in charge of an office of the firm must hold a license as a Public Accountant from the Department. 

Additionally, any partner, member of a limited liability company or shareholder of a corporation not personally engaged in practicing as a Public Accountant in this State must have obtained  a Certified Public Accountant (CPA) or otherwise be certified to practice accounting in some State or Territory of the United States, District of Columbia or in a foreign country or a political subdivision thereof.  120 hours of continuing professional education every 3 years is required for renewal of a license.
  </DD></DL><HR><H3>
VII. Fees:     </H3>
<DL><DD>Registration for Public Accountant: $75. <P><DD> Partnership: $75. <P><DD> Continuing Education Sponsor: $150
  </DD></DL>






<HR>
