<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Pharmacy Technician License</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. 	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Pharmacy Technician License
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II. 	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
Licensing & Testing Division<BR>
Health Services Section<BR>
320 West Washington, 3rd Floor<BR>
Springfield, Illinois 62786<BR>
(217) 524-7540<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 85/1-39 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Anyone directly assisting a licensed pharmacist in the practice of pharmacy must register with the Department.  Applicants must be at least 16 years of age and a high school graduate. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V. 	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Application forms are available from the Department by written request or by calling the Forms Unit at (217) 785-0842. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The application fee is $40 for an initial certification of registration and $25 annual renewal.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
