<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Registration for Athletic Trainer </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Registration for Athletic Trainer 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
Licensing & Testing Division<BR>
Professional Services Section<BR>
(217) 785-0894<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5/1- 34. Illinois Athletic Trainers Practice Act
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
68 Illinois Administrative Code, Chapter VII, subchapter b, Part 1160
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Athletic Trainers must be registered with the Department.<P>

Acting as an Athletic Trainer without registration with the Department is a Class A misdemeanor for the first offense and a Class 4 Felony for each subsequent offense.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must give proof of graduation from a 4 year accredited college or university, have completed a prescribed course of study established by the Athletic Training Board, and pass a written exam for Athletic Trainers.  After passing the examination, applicant may apply to the Department for a License. <P>

Licensure may be denied if education or experience is deficient. Applicants may apply for reconsideration within 35 days of the date of the denial notice by submitting additional or mitigating information to the Department. Denials may be appealed through the circuit court. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicant's course of study must have included at least one course in: Anatomy; Physiology; Physiology of Exercise; Applied Anatomy and Kinesiology; Psychology (2 Courses); First Aid and CPR or equivalent (American Red Cross standards); Nutrition; Remedial or Therapeutic Exercise; Personal, Community, and School Health; Techniques of Athletic training (modalities, administration). In addition to coursework requirements, a minimum of 800 hours of Clinical experience over a minimum 2 year period is required.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The application fee is $50 (in addition to any examination fees). <P>

Bi-Annual renewal for a license is $40.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
