<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Registration for Cosmetologist,  Cosmetologist Teacher and License for Cosmetology School</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. 	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Registration for Cosmetologist,  Cosmetologist Teacher and License for Cosmetology School
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
Licensing & Testing Division<BR>
Professional Services Section<BR>
(217) 785-0894<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 410/1 et seq.The Illinois Barber, Cosmetology, Esthetics and Nail Technology Act
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
68 Illinois Administrative Code Chapter VII, subchapter b Part 1175
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A Certificate of Registration from the Department is required in order to work as a Cosmetologist or be a Teacher of Cosmetology.  A License is required to operate a School of Cosmetology.  Conducting these businesses without a License or registration is a Class B Misdemeanor for the first offense, a Class A Misdemeanor for the second offense and a Class 4 Felony for each subsequent offense.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V. 	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A written exam is required for Cosmetologists and Cosmetology Teachers. Application forms are available from the Department's Springfield office.  Applications are sent to a testing service for preliminary review before candidates are scheduled to take the exam. Upon passing the exam, applicants will receive application forms to apply for a license. <P>

Denial of eligibility to take the exam is usually based on deficiencies in education or experience.<P>

Reconsideration may be requested within 35 days of the denial notice by submitting additional or mitigating information. Denials may be appealed by filing suit in the circuit court. Cosmetology School Licenses may be issued only after an on-site inspection of the proposed school site.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<EM>Cosmetologists</EM> - Must be at least 16,  have graduated from High School or possess a GED equivalent and be a graduate of an approved School of Cosmetology where they completed 1500 hours of study in Cosmetology. Successful completion of a written exam is required before Registration is granted.<P>

<EM>Cosmetology Teachers</EM> - Must be 18 years, have a High School diploma (or GED equivalent), be  registered as a Cosmetologist, have completed 500 hours of teacher training in a registered school of Cosmetology and 2 years practical experience as a registered cosmetologist or have completed 1,000 hours of teacher training in a licensed school of Cosmetology. Successful completion of a written exam is required before Registration is granted. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:  </H3>
<DL><DD>
Application for Licensure:			$ 25.<P>
Renewal of License:					$ 40.<P>
License Restoration & Lapsed Renewal: 	$ 10.<P>
Duplicate License:					$ 20.<P>
Certification of License:			$ 20.<P>
License for Cosmetology School:		$100.<P>

These fees are in addition to any examination fees.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

