<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Ambulatory Surgical Treatment Center (ASTC)</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.    Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Ambulatory Surgical Treatment Center (ASTC)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.   Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Public Health<BR>
Office of Health Care Regulation / Division of Health Facilities and Programs<BR>
525 West Jefferson<BR>
Springfield, IL 62761<BR>
(217) 782-7412<BR>
TDD:  1-800-547-0466 (for hearing impaired use only)<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
210 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5 (Ambulatory Surgical Treatment Center Act)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
77 Illinois Administrative Code 205   (Ambulatory Surgical Treatment Center Licensing Requirements)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3> 
<DL><DD>
A license is required to operate an Ambulatory Surgical Treatment Center (ASTC).<P> 

Licensure rules are elaborate and complex, covering items such as standards of professional work; policies and procedures; personnel qualifications; laboratory services; emergency, preoperative, operative and post operative care; clinical records; and physical plant.<P> 

License holders violating the Act are subject to an administrative hearing and revocation of the license. Licenses are valid for 1 year.<P> 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.   Approval Process:  </H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must file with the Department an "Ambulatory Surgical Treatment Center Licensure Application", a financial statement, a statement of ownership, architectural plans of the ASTC location, a completed transfer agreement with a hospital within 15 minutes travel time of the location, and a narrative description of the ASTC's proposed operation including examination procedures, surgical procedures performed and recovery protocols.  Applications are usually processed in 1 month.<P> 

Applications may be denied if the facilities, financing or staff are inadequate.<P> 

If an application is denied, applicants may correct the deficiencies and reapply. Inspections occur annually.<P> 

Licenses may be revoked or not issued if the moral character of the applicant, owner or manager is in question (if he/she has been convicted of a felony or of Medicaid or Medicare fraud, etc.); the ASTC is not under the medical supervision of a licensed physician; or the ASTC fails to comply with Act and rules. Municipalities may license these locations.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.   Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>  
<DL><DD>
A Certificate of Need (CON) is required from the Illinois Health Facilities Planning Board before a license application is submitted to the Department. 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.   Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<STRONG>Initial application fee:</STRONG> $500.<P>

<STRONG>Annual license fee:</STRONG> $300.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
