<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Asbestos Management Planner's License</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.  Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Asbestos Management Planner's License
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II. Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Public Health<BR>
Office of Health Protection<BR>
Division of Environmental Health / Asbestos Program<BR>
525 West Jefferson St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62761<BR>
(217) 782-3517<BR>
TDD:  1-800-547-0466 (hearing impaired use only)<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
105 Illinois Compiled Statutes 105/1 et seq. (Asbestos Abatement Act.)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
77 Illinois Administrative Code 855.40, 855.350 and 855 Appndx C, Illustration B.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A license is required to act as an Asbestos Management Planner to prepare asbestos management plans for public and private schools (grades 1-12). All school buildings are required by federal regulation to have an Asbestos Management Plan. License requirements ensure that persons who prepare asbestos management plans are qualified. Violations of code requirements may result in fines which vary with the severity of the violation.  Licenses expire  May 15 of each year. Licenses issued after January 15 expire May 15 the following year. 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must submit an application for licensure as an Asbestos Management Planner, two 1x1" photos, an Inspector's Training Course certificate or a current Inspector's refresher course certificate (if the initial course certificate has expired) and all expired Inspector refresher course certificates, a Management Planner Training Course certificate and a current Management Planner refresher course certificate, if the initial course certificate has expired, and all expired Management Planner refresher course certificates, a copy of an Illinois Architects License, Professional Engineer License, or a Structural Engineer License, or Industrial Hygienist Certificate; or a copy of a transcript and evidence of obtaining a bachelor's degree or higher in architecture, engineering, mathematics, or science or evidence of a bachelor's degree and meet the experience requirements for a licensed inspector of 1040 hours. Applicants with bachelor degrees in other areas must submit written verification of 4160 hours of experience in asbestos inspections, instruction, project management, project design, or other asbestos management and control activities. The Department processes the application in 60 days. 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must be licensed Architects, Professional Engineers, Structural Engineers or Industrial Hygienists or have a Bachelor's Degree or higher in architecture, engineering, mathematics, or science and meet experience requirements of an accredited inspector or Bachelor degree in another subject area and 4160 hours of experience.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.  Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<STRONG>Application fee:</STRONG> $50.<P> 

<STRONG>Renewal fee:</STRONG>  $50.<P>

A $15 late fee is assessed if the renewal application is not received by May 1.<P> 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
