<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Asbestos Worker's License</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Asbestos Worker's License
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Public Health<BR>
Office of Health Protection<BR>
Division of Environmental Health / Asbestos Program<BR>
525 West Jefferson St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62761<BR>
(217) 782-3517<BR>
TDD:  1-800-547-0466 (for hearing impaired use only)<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
105 Illinois Compiled Statutes 105/1 et seq. (Asbestos Abatement Act) and P.A. #89-143 (Commercial and Public Buildings Asbestos Abatement Act)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
77 Illinois Administrative Code 855.290 and 855 Appendix C Illustration G
</DD></DL>

<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
An asbestos worker license is required to clean, remove, encapsulate, enclose, repair, haul, or dispose of asbestos-containing building materials in public and private schools (grades 1-12) and commercial and public buildings. The purpose of the license is to insure that those working with asbestos in school buildings are properly trained. The license requirement applies to workers employed by Asbestos Abatement Contractors and maintenance workers employed by school districts, private schools or commercial or public buildings who may be required to disturb asbestos-containing materials in school buildings and commercial and public buildings. License holders failing to comply with Code requirements are subject to fines that vary with the severity of the violation.<P> 

Licenses expire January 31 of each year.  However, licenses issued between October 31 and February 1 expire the following January 31.<P> 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must file an application for licensure as an asbestos worker; two 1x1" photos of applicant, an asbestos worker training course certificate or an asbestos contractor/supervisor training course certificate, a copy of a current worker refresher certificate (if the worker initial course certificate is expired), a copy of a contractor/supervisor refresher certificate (if the initial contractor/suprevisor certificate is expired).<P> 

The Department usually processes applications in 15 days.<P> 

Applicants may correct any deficiencies and then reapply.<P>   
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must be 18. Licenses may be renewed by submitting a completed License Renewal Application and a certificate of completion of an approved refresher course completed within the 12 months previous to license expiration. Refresher courses are offered by independent training course providers, such as community colleges.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.  Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Application fee of $25 is required for an initial or renewal license.<P> 

Licenses that have been expired for less than 2 years may be reinstated by payment of all lapsed license fees plus a reinstatement fee of $15.<P> 
</DD></DL>


<HR>
