<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Community Living Facilities</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Community Living Facilities
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Public Health <BR> 
Office of Health Care Regulation / Bureau of Long-Term Care<BR>
525 West Jefferson<BR>
Springfield, IL 62761<BR>
(217) 782-2913<BR>
TDD:  1-800-547-0466 (for hearing impaired use only)<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
210 Illinois Compiled Statutes 35 (Community Living Facilities Licensing Act)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
77 Illinois Administrative Code 370 (Minimum Standards for the Licensure of Community Living Facilities)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.   Requirement Description:</H3>  
<DL><DD>
A license is required to operate a Community Living Facility. License rules include standards for administration, admission and discharge policies, personnel, medication, communicable disease and medical care policies, food service, social services and programming, and physical plant.<P> 

Licenses are valid for 1 year. <P>

Licenses may be revoked for violations of the Act.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.    Approval Process:</H3>  
<DL><DD>
Applicants must file a "Community Living Facilities Application", a written description of the proposed program, a statement of ownership, and a copy of the lease or management agreement (unless the applicant owns the building).<P>  

Applications usually take 1 month to process.<P> 

The Department inspects facilities annually at a minimum, and more often if deemed appropriate. Applications may be denied and licenses revoked for reasons including: cruelty or indifference to residents; unlawful appropriation or conversion of a resident's property; committing, permitting, aiding, or abetting the commission of any illegal act in the facility; failure to operate or conduct the facility in accordance with the Act and its minimum standards; submitting false information on the Department license forms or during an inspection.<P> 

Licenses may be revoked for the inclusion of a person in the ownership or management of the facility who was or is involved in the ownership or operation of a facility continually or repeatedly operated in substantial non-compliance with the Act or its minimum standards, refusing to allow an inspection to occur; violating the rights of residents, or failing to submit or implement a plan of correction within the specified time period.<P> 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.   Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites: </H3>
<DL><DD>
License holders also must comply with Department of Mental Health requirements.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.   Fees:  </H3>
<DL><DD>
<STRONG>Annual and initial license fee:</STRONG> $200.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
