<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Migrant Labor Camps</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.  Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Migrant Labor Camps
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Public Health<BR>
Division of Environmental Health / Office of Health Protection<BR>
Migrant Labor Camp Program<BR>
525 West Jefferson<BR>
Springfield, IL 62761<BR>
(217) 782-5830<BR>
TDD:  1-800-547-0466 (for hearing impaired use only)<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
210 Illinois Compiled Statutes 110/1-17  (Migrant Labor Camp Law)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
77 Illinois Administrative Code 935  (Migrant Labor Camp Code)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A license is required to operate migrant worker housing for 10 or more migrant workers, or 4 or more migrant workers and their family members.<P> 

A permit is required before construction may begin on a new migrant worker labor camp, or before  beginning a major alteration or extension of a licensed migrant labor camp.<P>

Licenses must be renewed annually.<P>

Violations of the Migrant Labor Camp Law are a Class A misdemeanor.<P> 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Plans must be submitted to the Department together with an application to construct a migrant labor camp before construction may begin for a new camp or an expansion of an existing camp.<P>

Applications are approved or disapproved by the Department within 2 weeks of receipt.<P> 

A license application to operate a migrant labor camp must be filed with the Department at least 60 days prior the opening of a camp.  Upon receipt of an application for a License to operate a camp the Department will inspect camp housing units for compliance with the Law and Code rules.  Licensed camps are inspected once before occupancy and once a year thereafter.<P>  

License holders must comply with Code requirements including sanitary conditions, waste and water disposal.<P>

License holders must file a renewal application and pass an annual Department inspection before a License will be renewed.<P>  

A License can be suspended or revoked and the camp closed for violations.  Penalties are assessed based on the severity and duration of an offense.<P>
</DD></DL> 

<HR>
<H3>VI.   Pre-Requisites, Co.-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.  Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
$100 original license fee; $100 annual license renewal fee.<P>

There is no fee for a Permit for construction, alteration or expansion of camp facilities.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
