<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Mobile Home Parks (Construction Permit & Annual License)</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.  Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Mobile Home Parks (Construction Permit & Annual License)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Public Health<BR>
Division of Environmental Health / Office of Health Protection<BR>
Mobile Home Park Program<BR>
525 West Jefferson<BR>
Springfield, IL 62761<BR>
(217) 782-5830<BR>
TDD:  1-800-547-0466 (for hearing impaired use only)<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
210 Illinois Compiled Statutes 115/1-27 (Mobile Home Park Act)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
77 Illinois Administrative Code 860 (Mobile Home Park Code)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A permit is required to construct a new mobile home park or expand an existing mobile home park.<P> 

A license is required to operate a mobile home park with 5 or more mobile home sites. (mobile home parks located in home rule units of government are exempt from these requirements.)<P> 

Operating without a license or construction without a permit is a Class B misdemeanor.<P> 

Licenses are valid for 1 year.<P>
</DD></DL>  

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must submit a permit application to construct mobile home park together with construction plans bearing the seal of a registered Illinois professional engineer or architect.<P> 

Plans are usually reviewed within 2 weeks. If the permit and plans are satisfactory, a permit is issued and construction may begin. Applicants must then submit an application to operate a mobile home park to the Department. Before the license is issued the Department inspects the site for compliance with the rules. Once a license is issued, the applicant must adhere to all safety and sanitation code requirements as specified in the code.<P>

If the license application is denied, the applicant can attempt to correct the deficiencies and then reapply.<P> 

Mobil home parks are inspected annually by the Department prior to renewal of the annual license.<P>  

Licenses are denied or revoked if code violations are not corrected within a specified time period.<P> 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.  Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Plan Review			$50<P>
License 				$100 plus $3 per site<P>
Late fees				$50 (applies to renewal applications submitted after April 30)<P> 
New mobile home sites	$6<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
