<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Modular Dwellings & Commercial Mobile Structures</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.  Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Modular Dwellings & Commercial Mobile Structures
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Public Health<BR>
Division of Environmental Health / Office of Health Protection<BR>
Manufactured Housing Program<BR>
525 West Jefferson<BR>
Springfield, IL 62761<BR>
(217) 782-5830<BR>
TDD:  1-800-547-0466 (for hearing impaired use only)<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
430 Illinois Compiled Statutes 115/1-15 (Manufactured Housing and Mobile Home Safety Act )
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
77 Illinois Administrative Code 880 (Manufactured Housing and Mobile Structures Code) 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A plan approval is required to construct modular dwellings, duplex mobile homes or commercial mobile structures in Illinois. Construction without approval is a Class B misdemeanor. 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must submit detailed plans bearing the seal of  an Illinois Registered Architect (this is not required for modular dwellings) indicating compliance with the building codes. <P>

The Department issues approval if the application is satisfactory.<P> 

Plans are usually reviewed and a permit issued within one week after an application is received.<P> 

If an application is denied, applicant can correct the problems and reapply.<P> 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A seal issued by the Department must be placed on each approved structure upon completion of the construction and the "Code Compliance Certificate" must be completed and returned to the Department when the structure is placed at a location in Illinois.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.  Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
$150 for Plan Review for a model group and $25 for each specific model.<P>
$25 for each seal to be attached to approved structures.<P>
$25 for each Code Compliance Certificate.<P>
</DD></DL>


<HR>
