<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Structural Pest Control (Business License; Registration of Non-commercial locations; Certification of Technicians.)</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>


<H3>I.  Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Structural Pest Control (Business License; Registration of Non-commercial locations; Certification of Technicians.)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Public Health<BR>
Division of Environmental Health / Office of Health Protection<BR>
Structural Pest Control Program<BR>
525 West Jefferson<BR>
Springfield, IL 62761<BR>
(217) 782-5830<BR>
TDD:  1-800-547-0466 (for hearing impaired use only)<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 235/1-25 (Structural Pest Control Act)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
77 Illinois Administrative Code 830 (Structural Pest Control Code)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Commercial businesses that perform structural pest control (SPC) services for hire, using general-use or restricted pesticides must be licensed by the Department. Operating without a license is a Class A misdemeanor. Licenses are valid for 1 year. Non-commercial locations (businesses whose employees use restricted pesticides at the business location, such as food plants, housing authorities, etc.) must be registered with Department. Licenses are valid for 1 year.   Structural Pest Control Technicians must be certified by the Department by passing an exam regarding the use of pesticides.  Certification is valid for 3 years.<P>

Failure to comply with the requirements of the Illinois Administrative Code (Code) may result in fines which differ according to the severity of the violation.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants for a Commercial SPC Business license must submit an application for a structural pest control business license to the Department. Licenses are usually issued within 1 week. Upon issuance of a license, the holder must observe all Code requirements. If an application is denied, the applicant may reapply.<P>  

Applicants for Non-commercial SPC registration must submit  an application for registration as a non-commercial structural pest control location. Approval of registration is usually granted within 1 week if all requirements are met.  Certification as an SPC technician, requires an application for certification as a structural pest control technician (either "general" or "restricted") at least 30 days prior to the exam date. Certificates are issued within 2 weeks.<P>	
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisite & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Commercial businesses must have at least 1 certified technician to use or oversee the use of pesticides and must provide proof of liability coverage for bodily injury and property damage. <P>

Non-commercial locations must have a technician who is certified to use restricted pesticides. Technicians taking the exam for general use pesticides are required to have a high school diploma or GED certificate. Those taking 1 or more of the 8 sub-category exams for restricted pesticides must also have 6 months experience, 16 semester hours of college credit in entomology or related subjects or, have completed a Department approved pest control course.  <P>

Technicians must attend at least 1 Department approved recertification seminar during the 3 year period covered by the certification.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
New/Renewed Commercial Business Licenses: $100.<BR>
New/Renewed Non-Commercial Business Registration: $50.<BR>
Original exams: $40.<BR>
Reexamination: $40.<BR>
Renewal of technician certification: $40.<BR>
All late renewal fees: $75.<BR>
All duplicate licenses: $10.<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
