<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Youth Camps (Construction Permit & Annual License)</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.    Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Youth Camps (Construction Permit & Annual License)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.   Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Public Health<BR>
Division of Environmental Health / Office of Health Protection<BR>
Youth Camp Program<BR>
525 West Jefferson<BR>
Springfield, IL 62761<BR>
(217) 782-5830<BR>
TDD:  1-800-547-0466 (for hearing impaired use only)<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
210 Illinois Compiled Statutes 100/1-23  (Youth Camp Act )
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
77 Illinois Administrative Code 810 (Youth Camp Code)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A Construction Permit from the Department is required before construction of a new youth camp or expansion of an existing youth camp.<P> 

A license is required from the Department to operate a youth camp.<P> 

A "Youth Camp" is subject to licensing if it provides overnight camping for 5 or more youths under the age of 18 for at least 5 days a year.<P> 

Operating without a license is a Class A misdemeanor.<P> 

Licenses are valid for 1 year and are renewable.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.   Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Construction plans for a new or expansion of an existing youth camp must be submitted to the Department with an permit application to construct at a youth camp prior to the beginning of construction.<P> 

Plans are usually reviewed within 2 weeks of receipt.<P> 

Construction may not begin until a permit is issued. When construction is complete, an inspection of the facilities is performed to determine compliance with Code requirements. If the conditions are satisfactory, applicants must submit an application for licensure of a youth camp to the Department for approval.<P> 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License holders must report to the Department any deaths and any injuries which require a physician's care that occur at the Youth Camp.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<STRONG>Annual license fee:</STRONG> $25. Governmental entities are exempt from the fee.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
