<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Occupation License</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement  Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Occupation License
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Racing Board<BR>
100 West Randolph; Suite 11-100<BR>
Chicago, IL 60601<BR>
(312) 814-2600<BR>
TDD:  (312) 814-5039<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
230 Illinois Compiled Statutes, 5/9(b)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Title 11, Illinois Administrative Code, Subtitle B, Chapter I, Part502
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Within the Illinois Horse Racing Industry there are several occupations which require licensure by the Illinois Racing Board for: Owners, Trainers & Assistant Trainers, Prospective Trainers, Jockeys & Apprentice Jockeys, Harness Drivers, Veterinarians & Veterinary Assistants, Ferriers(Blacksmiths), Exercise Riders, Pony Persons, Stable Foreman, Jockey Agents, Authorized Agents, Tack Shop Operators & Other Vendors, Vender Helpers, Thoroughbred & Harness Grooms, Hotwalker & Totalizator Employees. No person may participate in a race meeting unless he/she is properly licensed. <P>

Possible penalties for violating the rules and regulations include: fines not to exceed $5,000 for each violation and/or suspension from activities at one or more race tracks. <P>

Each occupation license is valid for one year and expires every December 31. An occupational license issued at one race meeting during the calendar year is also valid at any other race meeting regulated by the Board that year.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Any person desiring an occupation license must apply on forms provided by the Illinois Racing Board.  The applicant may at the Board's request, be required to submit supplemental information if it helps determine eligibility or qualification.  The applications may be obtained from the license office at any race track regulated by the Board or at the address and phone # listed above. License applications are usually processed in one day.<P>

Common reasons for denial include:  giving false answers on the application, having a suspended or revoked license in another racing jurisdiction or violating the Board's rules or the Act. <P>

If an application is denied by the Board, the applicant may request a hearing before the Board or be ineligible to reapply for a license for one calendar year.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:  </H3>
<DL><DD>
An applicant, other than a corporation, for an occupation license shall be at least 16 years old.<P>

An applicant shall furnish with the license application two sets of classifiable fingerprints.<P>

An applicant for an occupation license in all categories, except that of Owner, shall be a U.S. citizen, a permanent resident alien, or holder of a permanent work permit.<P>

While in the stable area of a race track, all occupation licensees shall wear their identification cards prominently displayed on their outer garments.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
(License fees are Non-Refundable.)<P>

$25	Owner, Trainer, Owner/Trainer, Owner/Trainer/Driver, Driver, Jockey, Jockey Apprentice, Jockey Agent, Veterinarian, Farrier, Apprentice Farrier, Authorized Agent, Vendor, Partnership, Starter, Totalizator and Racing Official<P>

$15	Assistant Trainer & Assistant Veterinarian<P>

$10	Excercise Person, Pony Person, Foreman & Vendor Helper<P>

$5	Hotwalker & Grooms<P>
</DD></DL>


<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
