<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Chicago Home Rule Municipal Soft Drink Retailer's Occupation Tax</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:	</H3>
<DL><DD>Chicago Home Rule Municipal Soft Drink Retailer's Occupation Tax</DD></DL><HR>
<H3>II.	Agency: </H3>
<DL><DD>Illinois Department of Revenue<BR>
101 West Jefferson St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794<BR>
Taxpayer Services Bureau<BR>
Central Registration Division<BR>
(217) 785-3707</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:  </H3>
<DL><DD>65 Illinois Compiled Statutes, 5/8-11-66.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>  
<DL><DD><P>Chicago Home Rule Municipal Soft Drink Retailer's Occupation Tax is imposed on businesses located in Chicago selling finished, ready-to-use, non-alcoholic drinks, whether carbonated or not, contained in a closed or sealed bottle, can, carton, or container of any size, including those dispensed from vending machines.  Businesses must register with the Department and receive a certificate authorizing them to collect and remit the Tax.

<P>Conducting business without registering, or failure to collect and remit any and all taxes due, is a Class A Misdemeanor and may result in penalties that include, but are not limited to:  A tax lien against property, garnishment of wages and bank accounts, recommendation of professional license revocation, civil judgment, revocation of business certificates of registration, withholding of state warrants, seizure and sale of assets, nonrenewal of corporate charter and/or criminal prosecution.

<P>The certificate of registration is effective for 5 years.  If a business remains in compliance, the Department will automatically issue a renewal.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:  </H3>
<DL><DD>Applicants must complete and file with the Department an Illinois Business Taxpayer Registration Application (NUC-1).  The average processing time is 3 weeks.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites: </H3> 
<DL><DD>Registered businesses must file an annual report form ST-14.  A Federal Employer Identification Number (FEIN) may be required.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees: </H3>
<DL><DD>There is no registration fee.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
