<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Coin-Operated Amusement Device and Redemption Machine License.</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile: </H3>
<DL><DD>Coin-Operated Amusement Device and Redemption Machine License.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:  </H3>
<DL><DD>Illinois Department of Revenue<BR>
101 West Jefferson St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794<BR>
Taxpayer Services Bureau<BR>
Miscellaneous Taxes Division<BR>
Cashiering & Batch Control Section<BR>
(217) 785-5862</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute :  </H3>
<P>35 Illinois Compiled Statutes 35/510. 
<H3>Regulation: </H3>
<DL><DD>Title 86, Illinois Administrative Code, Chapter I, Section 460.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description :  </H3>
<DL><DD>This license is required for operators of amusement machine devices and redemption machines (pin-ball machines are typical examples).  These licenses are most typically required by video arcades, taverns, bowling alleys, and similar businesses.  By obtaining the license a business becomes properly registered with the Department.  Any amusement device not properly licensed is subject to a penalty, and may be seized by the Department.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process: </H3>
<DL><DD>Applicants must complete Form RCOA-2, Coin-Operated Amusement Device Application for License, and remit the proper tax.  Applications are usually processed within two weeks.  Applications for licenses must be submitted prior to July 31 every year. Licenses, in the form of decals, are issued by the Department and must be applied to machines prior to placing the machines in service.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:  </H3>
<DL><DD>Decals must be displayed on the machines.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees: </H3>
<DL><DD><P>The license fee is $15 for machines placed in service on or after August 1 of any year and prior to February 1 of the succeeding year. 
<P> The license fee is $8 for machines placed in service on or after February 1 of any year and ending July 31 of the same year.</DD></DL>

<HR>
