<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Use Tax Registration</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
	<DL><DD>Use Tax Registration</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>Illinois Department of Revenue<BR>
101 West Jefferson St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794<BR>
Taxpayer Services Bureau<BR>
Central Registration Division<BR>
(217) 785-3707</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>35 Illinois Compiled Statutes, 105/1</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>86 Illinois Administrative Code, Section 150.101.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD><P>The Use Tax applies to sales of goods , merchandise, equipment and supplies from out-of-state vendors, purchased in Illinois by residents for their own use.  Registration authorizes collection and remittance to the Department of the Use Tax.  Conducting business without registering, or failure to collect and remit the tax, is a Class A Misdemeanor and may result in penalties including, but not limited to the following:  A lien against property, garnishment of wages and bank accounts, recommendation of professional license revocation, civil judgment, revocation of business certificates of registration, withholding of state warrants, seizure and sale of assets, nonrenewal of corporate charter and/or criminal prosecution.

<P>A certificate of registration issued by the Department is effective for 5 years.  If a business remains in compliance, the Department will automatically issue a renewal.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD> An applicant must complete and file with the Department an Illinois Business Taxpayer Registration Application (NUC-1).  The average processing time is 3 weeks.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:  </H3>
<DL><DD>Certificate holders must file an annual report on form ST-1.  A Federal Employer Identification Number (FEIN) may be required.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:  </H3>
<DL><DD>There is no fee for a certificate of registration.</DD></DL>

