<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: MPEA (Metropolitan Pier Exposition Authority) Food and Beverage Tax</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>	
<DL><DD>MPEA (Metropolitan Pier Exposition Authority) Food and Beverage Tax</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency: </H3>
<DL><DD>Illinois Department of Revenue<BR>
101 West Jefferson St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794<BR>
Taxpayer Services Bureau<BR>
Central Registration Division<BR>
(217) 785-3707</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute :  </H3>
<DL><DD>70 Illinois Compiled Statutes, 210/13(B).</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description: </H3>
<DL><DD><P>Metropolitan Pier Exposition Authority (MPEA) Food and Beverage Tax applies to businesses that sell at retail, food, alcoholic beverages, and/or soft drinks within the Chicago MPEA boundaries, for immediate consumption either on or off the premises.  Businesses must register with the Department and receive a certificate of authorization to collect and remit the MPEA Food and Beverage Tax.

<P>Conducting business without registering with the Department, or failure to collect and remit taxes is a Class A Misdemeanor, and may result in penalties including, but not limited to: A tax lien against property, garnishment of wages and bank accounts, recommendation of professional license revocation, civil judgment, revocation of business certificates of registration, withholding of state warrants, seizure and sale of assets, nonrenewal of corporate charter and/or criminal prosecution.

<P>The certificate is effective for 5 years from the date of its issuance or last renewal.  If the business remains in compliance, the Department will automatically renew a certificate.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process: </H3>
<DL><DD>An applicant must complete and file with the Department an Illinois Business Taxpayer Registration Application (NUC-1).  The average processing time is 3 weeks.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites: </H3>
<DL><DD>Registered businesses must file annual report forms ST-4 / ST-7.  A Federal Employer Identification Number (FEIN) may be required.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:  </H3>
<DL><DD>There is no registration fee.</DD></DL>

<HR>
