<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Hotel Tax Certificate of Registration</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>Hotel Tax Certificate of Registration</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:  </H3>
<DL><DD>Illinois Department of Revenue<BR>
101 West Jefferson St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794<BR>
Taxpayer Services Bureau<BR>
Miscellaneous Taxes Division<BR>
Registration & Returns Processing Section<BR>
(217) 785-5863</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:  </H3>
<DL><DD>35 Illinois Compiled Statutes 145. </DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation: </H3>
<DL><DD>86 Illinois Administrative Code 1/480.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:  </H3>
<DL><DD><P>A Hotel Tax Certificate of Registration is required for businesses renting, leasing or letting rooms to persons for living quarters (such as hotels, motels, inns, bed & breakfasts).  By obtaining this Certificate a business becomes properly registered with the Department to collect and remit the Hotel Operator's Occupation Tax Act.  It is unlawful to rent, lease, or let rooms in Illinois without a Certificate of Registration.

<P>Certificates are nontransferable and must be returned to the Department if the business is sold or discontinued.  If the business entity changes or a new Federal Employer Identification Number (FEIN) is issued, the business must re-register with the Department and re-apply for a new certificate of registration.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:  </H3>
<DL><DD>Applicants for a Hotel Tax Certificate must complete and file with the Department a "Hotel Operator's Occupation Tax Application" (Form RHM-2).  If the taxpayer has multiple locations, an application must be filed for each location.  The average processing time for the application is two weeks.  A Surety Bond in the amount of three times the estimated monthly tax must be filed with the application.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:  </H3>
<DL><DD>Taxpayers must file a Hotel Operator's Occupation Tax Return (Form RHM-1) by the end of each month, unless the Department authorizes annual filings.  If a hotel is selling telecommunications services to guests at retail, it also must register under the Telecommunications Excise Tax Act.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:  </H3>
<DL><DD>There are no fees for a Hotel Tax Certificate of Registration</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
