<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Prepaid Sales Tax (PST)</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:	</H3>
<DD>Prepaid Sales Tax (PST)</DD>
<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency: </H3>
<DL><DD>Illinois Department of Revenue<BR>
101 West Jefferson St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794<BR>
Taxpayer Services Bureau<BR>
Central Registration Division<BR>
(217) 785-3707</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute: </H3>
<DL><DD>35 Illinois Compiled Statutes, 120/2D.</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:  </H3>
<DL><DD>Title 86 Illinois Administrative Code, Section 130.551.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:  </H3>
<DL><DD><P>Motor fuel distributors, suppliers, or resellers, or resellers selling motor fuel to retailers are required by law to collect and remit to the Department the Prepaid Sales Tax.  (The most typical example of this requirement occurs when a motor fuel distributor sells motor fuel to a service station.).  Businesses must register with the Department in order to collect and remit the Tax.

<P>Conducting these businesses without registering with the Department, or of not collecting and remitting taxes, is a Class A Misdemeanor and may result in the Department taking further action against the business, including, but not limited to: filing a tax lien against property, garnishment of wages and bank accounts, recommendation of professional license revocation, civil judgments, revocation of business certificates of registration, withholding of state warrants, seizure and sale of assets and criminal prosecution.

<P>A certificate of registration is effective for 5 years if the business is a retailer, and 3 years if the business is a reseller.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:  </H3>
<DL><DD>To become registered, the applicant must complete the Illinois Business Taxpayer Registration Application (NUC-1).  The average processing time for the application is 3 weeks.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites: </H3>
<DL><DD>Certificate holders must file annual report forms PST-1 and PST-2.  A Federal Employer Identification Number (FEIN) may be required.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:  </H3>
<DL><DD>There is no registration fee.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
