<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Investment Adviser Registration</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Investment Adviser Registration
</DD></DL>

<HR>	
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Secretary of State Securities Department Registration Division<BR>
900 South Spring St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62704<BR>
(217) 782-2256<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
815 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5/8D (Illinois Securities Law of 1953) 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV:	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Persons engaging in the business of advising others, for compensation, either directly or through publications or writings as to the value of securities or the advisability of investing in, purchasing or selling securities, or who promulgate analysis or reports concerning securities, must be registered with the Secretary of State.  Conducting business in violation of these requirements may be a Class A Misdemeanor or a Class 4 felony. Registration is valid for one year.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
An application for registration must be filed with the Secretary on Uniform Form ADV together with an unaudited balance sheet.  The application must set forth applicant's education background, business affiliations, his or her basis of compensation, whether applicant has been convicted of a felony or misdemeanor of which fraud is an essential element, as well as other pertinent information.<P>

Applicant must meet the requirements of one of following: Chartered Financial Analyst (CFA), Chartered Investment Counselor (CIC), Chartered Financial Consultant (ChFC), Certified Financial Planner (CFP) or pass the Series 2 or 7 and Series 65 exam.  If a review of the application shows it to be complete and accurate, and that the applicant has atleast one examination-qualified principal who will supervise investment advisory activities in the State, the applicant is registered.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Registrants must re-register annually.  Registrants must file an audited financial statement within 90 days after the end of the registrant's fiscal year end (if the adviser holds client's cash or securities).  Registrants must file an Illinois Principal Form annually, and an Illinois Branch Office From for each of his or her offices in the State of Illinois.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<STRONG><EM>Application:</EM></STRONG>  $200 a year plus $10 for each Representative not registered as a salesperson.<P>

<STRONG><EM>Annual renewal:</EM></STRONG> $200 plus $10 for each Representative not registered as a salesperson.<P>

<STRONG><EM>Annual Branch Office fee:</EM></STRONG>  $20 for each office in this State.<P>
</DD></DL>


<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
