<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Lobbyist Registration and Reporting</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.  Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Lobbyist Registration and Reporting
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II. Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Secretary of State<BR>
Index Department<BR>
111 East Monroe Street<BR>
Springfield, IL 62756<BR>
(217) 782-7017<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
25 Illinois Compiled Statutes170
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
2 Illinois Administrative Code 560
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV:  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The purpose of this Act is to regulate persons who directly communicate with legislators, constitutional officers, and other officials, such as agency directors, deputy directors, and general counsels, for the ultimate purpose of influencing an executive, legislative, or administrative action.  This Act may affect any business that does business with the State.  A business may be required to register if any salaried or contractual employee, as any part of their job duties, undertakes to influence the outcome of an executive, legislative, or administrative action.<P>

The employee would be required to register as an attachment to the
business' registration.  (Section 560.210 of the Code explains exemptions
from the Act).  The Secretary of State's Office does not have the statutory
authority to make the determination as to whether a business falls within
the purview of the Act and parties unsure as to whether the Act applies to
their business should consult with their lawyer. All registration
statements expire on December 31, and must be renewed by January 31.  The
primary purpose of this Act is to disclose expenditures (travel and
lodging, meals, beverages, entertainment, gifts and honoraria) on behalf of
officials by businesses subject to the Act.  Violations are a business
offense; parties convicted may be prohibited from lobbying for 3 years.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Registration Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Businesses must file a Registration Statement with an attachment for each employee who lobbies solely on behalf of the business.  It is not necessary to file an attachment for contractual lobbyists who are registered on their own or with another entity. (The Index Department provides a free "lobbyist packet" which contains rules, registration and reporting forms, and "A Guide to Lobbyist Registration and Reporting," with a copy of the Act.)
</DD></DL>

<H3>VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Registered, authorized agents are responsible for filing a semi-annual expenditure report by July 31 for the period of January 1 through June 30, or the final day of the General Assembly session, and an annual expenditure report by January 31 for the entire previous calendar year. Reports must be filed even if the business did not make reportable expenditures.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.  Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Registration fee for the business: $50, plus $50 registration fee for each salaried employee lobbying on behalf of the business (contractual lobbyists with other clients pay in conjunction with their own registration).  Registration statements and expenditure reports received within 15 days of a filing deadline must be accompanied by a $50 late filing fee.<P>

Registration statements and expenditure Reports received after 15 days of a
filing deadline are subject to an additional $100 penalty.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
