<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Registration of Securities Salespersons</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Registration of Securities Salespersons
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Secretary of State Securities Department Registration Division<BR>
900 South Spring St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62704<BR>
(217) 782-2256<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
815 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5/8 (Illinois Securities Law of 1953)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV:	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Salespersons must be registered with the Secretary before he or she may be employed by a securities dealer or issuer to offer, purchase or sell securities.  Salespersons must be 18 years of age,.  Registration is valid for a calendar year; expires on December 31, and must be renewed annually.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applications to register a salesperson must be filed by a registered dealer, issuer or "controlling person" (defined in 815 ILCS 5/2.2).  Applicants must complete and file on behalf of the candidate-salesperson a Uniform Form U-5,  a Securities Audit describing any civil or criminal proceedings of which fraud is an essential element pending against the candidate-salesperson, and applicable fees with the NASD.<P>  

Applications must include a statement that the salesperson is, or is about to be, employed by the applicant.  The candidate-salesperson must pass the Series 7 General Securities Representative examination and the Series 63 Uniform Securities Agent State Law examination.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Changes in the information stated in an application for registration or re-registration which is no longer accurate must be reported to the Secretary of State within 10 days after the change occurs.  A registered salesperson may move from one dealer to another by giving notice to the Secretary. 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<STRONG><EM>Application:</EM></STRONG>  $50.00<P>
<STRONG><EM>Renewal:</EM></STRONG>  $50.00.
</DD></DL>


<HR>
