<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Remitters License</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.     Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Remitters License
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.   Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Office of the Secretary of State of Illinois<BR>
Vehicle Services Department<BR>
Dealer/Remitter Licensing Section<BR>
Howlett Building, Room 069<BR>
Springfield, IL  62756<BR>
(217) 782-7817<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
625 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5/3-900
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Title 92 Illinois Administrative Code Chapter II, Section 1019
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
This license is required of anyone in the business of accepting money for remittance to the State or its instrumentalities, political subdivisions or to any of their officials, for payment of vehicle taxes, vehicle licenses or registration fees.  <P>

Licenses are valid for one year and may be renewed.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.   Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must complete and file a signed, notarized application with 2 affidavits form two individuals in the city or town of applicant's residence, a Remittance Agent's Bond in the amount of $10,000 and applicable fees.  A separate license is required for each location where business will be conducted.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License holders must maintain records prescribed by the law.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<STRONG><EM>Remitter's License:</EM></STRONG>   $50.
</DD></DL>




<HR>
