<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Securities Dealer Registration</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Securities Dealer Registration
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Secretary of State Securities Department Registration Division<BR>
900 South Spring St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62704<BR>
(217) 782-2256<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
815 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5/8C.  (Illinois Securities Law of 1953)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Persons engaging directly or indirectly, as agent, broker or principal, in the business of offering, selling, buying and selling or otherwise dealing or trading in securities must be registered with the Secretary of State.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must be at least 18 years old and have passed the Series 24-General Securities, Principal Plus Series 63-Uniform Securities Agent State Law Examination given by the National Association of Securities Dealers (NASD).  The application for registration must be filed on Uniform Form BD together with an unaudited balance sheet, and historical information including the nature and places of past business, a description of civil or criminal proceedings, felony convictions or misdemeanor charges of which fraud is an essential element, pending against applicant.<P>

If it is determined that the information required by the Act is complete and accurate, and that the applicant has at least one examination-qualified principal who will supervise sales activities in the State, the applicant is registered.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Changes that render information on the application inaccurate must be reported to the Secretary within 10 business days after the occurrence of the change.  An audited financial statement must be filed no later than 90 days after the end of the registrant's fiscal year.  An Illinois Principal Form must be filed.  An Illinois Branch Office Form must be filed for each office in the State.  Registrants must file for re-registration annually.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<STRONG><EM>Initial filing fee:</EM></STRONG>  $300<P>
<STRONG><EM>Annual re-registration fee:</EM></STRONG> $300<P>
<STRONG><EM>Branch office fee:</EM></STRONG> $20 for each office in this State.<P>

Late fees are assessed when the required forms or fees are not timely filed or paid.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
