<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.     Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Vehicle Auctioneer License
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.   Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Office of the Secretary of State of Illinois<BR>
Vehicle Services Department<BR>
Dealer/Remitter Licensing Section<BR>
Howlett Building, Room 069<BR>
Springfield, IL  62756<BR>
(217) 782-7817<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute :</H3>
<DL><DD>
625 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5/5-700
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV:  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A License is required for a person to engage in the business of auctioning vehicles for more than one owner.  (Exceptions to this requirement are municipalities and licensed vehicle dealers.)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
