<h3>
Department of Commerce & Community Affairs<p>
</h3>
<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4><p>
<font size=+3>1996 News Releases</font>
<br clear=right>
<hr>
<h3 align=center>
June 28, 1996<p>
</h3>

<H3 align=center>Chicagland Evecutives to Join Sister City Trade Mission to Birmingham, England</H3>

For Further Information , Contact:  Forbes Robertson @ 312-467-0602<p>

<strong>Chicago (June 28, 1996)</strong>-- On September 22-25, Chicago and Midwest executives, under the sponsorship of Mayor Richard M. Daley and the Lord Mayor of Birmingham, will examine firsthand the trade and investment opportunities in the West Midlands of the U.K. and Continental Europe.  The high-profile Mission is hosted by senior U.K. CEO's and trade organization leaders, plus U.K.-based American executives who have successfully developed new markets in the manufacturing heartland of the U.K.<p>

Birmingham, Chicago's Sister City, presents a dynamic location for U.S. companies interested in entering the U.K. market, expanding international operations, trading with an overseas partner, or seeking entry to the European Common Market.  This vital Trade Mission features on-site visits, one-on-one meetings, and details the critical paths to investing and trading in Europe.<p>

Birmingham, the U.K.'s second-largest city, is a strategically located transportation, financial, legal and marketing hub.  Known as a key gateway to Europe, Birmingham offers a skilled work force, competitive labor costs, and tax incentives for new investment.<p>

The September, 1996 Trade and Investment Mission is also sponsored by American Airlines; British-American Chamber of Commerce for the Midwest, Inc.; British Consulate-General, Chicago; Chicago-Birmingham Sister City Committee; Chicagoland Chamber of Commerce; Chicago Sister Cities International Program; City of Birmingham, Chicago Office; Hyatt Regency Hotel, Birmingham; Mid-America Committee; West Midlands Development Agency and The World Trade Center Chicago Association.  For further information contact: Forbes Robertson, City of Birmingham, Chicago Office, at the above number.<p>


