<h3>
Department of Commerce & Community Affairs<p>
</h3>
<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4><p>
<font size=+3>1996 News Releases</font>
<br clear=right>
<hr>
<h3 align=center>
May 10, 1996<p>
Conference to Honor Top Illinois Exporters
</h3>

<em>CHICAGO, IL</em> - Gov. Jim Edgar today urged established Illinois exporters as well as companies considering marketing their products or services abroad to attend the second annual "Crossing International Borders" conference May 16 in Chicago.<p>

"Illinois exports are at an all-time high," the Governor said.  "Our efforts to provide export assistance to Illinois companies helped boost sales of Illinois products in the global marketplace to more than $32 billion in 1995, as increase of 23.6 percent.  This conference is part of my administration's commitment to continued export excellence and even greater success for Illinois business."<p>

Highlights of the conference include presentation of the 1996 Governor's Export Awards to outstanding Illinois exporters and the keynote luncheon speech by Casey Cowell, Chairman, Chief Executive Officer and President of U.S. Robotics.<p>

Lt. Gov. Bob Kustra, the Governor's senior advisor for economic development, will open the conference.<p>

"The international marketplace holds tremendous opportunities for Illinois companies," Kustra said.  "Whether a business is a new to exporting or a sophisticated global company, 'Crossing Illinois Borders' is designed to help them explore the potential for overseas investment and export growth."<p>

The conference is the result of a public/private partnership between the Illinois Department of Commerce and Community Affairs (DCCA) and Arthur Andersen, the leading global accounting firm.<p>

Sessions will be led by experts in the international investment and exporting fields, including directors of the State of Illinois foreign offices, Arthur Andersen professionals and Illinois business executives.<p>

In addition, Illinois non-profit and government organizations, as well as companies providing services to Illinois exporters, will be available for consultation at the Illinois Export Forum, held in conjunction with the conference.<p>

More information about attending "Crossing International Borders" can be obtained by calling 312/507-9664 or 800/419-0667 (TDD).<p>

<HR>
